Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.59,0:00:12.39,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,这个剧本和我以前见过的任何剧本都不一样。。。\N{\r原文字幕}The script was unlike any\NI'd ever seen before...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.46,0:00:14.46,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,但我们能认出的是。。。\N{\r原文字幕}but what was recognizable about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.53,0:00:17.76,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,主要人物之间的关系。\N{\r原文字幕}were the relationships\Nbetween the main characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.84,0:00:19.00,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,我认识的。\N{\r原文字幕}That I recognized.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.07,0:00:21.30,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,你觉得她怎么样，韩？\N{\r原文字幕}What do you\Nthink of her, Han?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.37,0:00:22.74,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,我尽量不去，孩子。\N{\r原文字幕}I'm trying not to, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.84,0:00:24.83,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\r原文字幕}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.91,0:00:26.47,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,都在剧本里。\N{\r原文字幕}It was all in that screenplay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.54,0:00:28.81,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,The humor was there.幽默就在那里。心就在那里。\N{\r原文字幕}The heart was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.88,0:00:31.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Still, she's got a lot of spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.78,0:00:36.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We had a pirate, and we had a wizard,\Nand we had a farm boy and a princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.66,0:00:40.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And we had bickering robots,\Nand I thought, ''What's not to like?''
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.74,0:00:53.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was a form of popular storytelling\Nthat allowed you to...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.14,0:00:58.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,enter the world of the characters\Nand to enjoy the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.28,0:01:05.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It has become a cultural phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.95,0:01:07.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Its motifs, phrases...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.42,0:01:08.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,May the Force be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.92,0:01:10.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and characters are a part of\Nthe consciousness...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.89,0:01:13.62,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,of millions of people\Naround the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.69,0:01:17.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Though the Star Wars universe might\Nseem to have sprung fully formed...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.63,0:01:19.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,from the consciousness\Nof George Lucas...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.90,0:01:22.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the truth is it might've been\Na very different place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.03,0:01:25.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Originally, the story\Nwas about Luke Starkiller.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.17,0:01:27.73,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And Starkiller\Nwas ultimately the father...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.84,0:01:31.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and the twins were his kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.78,0:01:36.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That eventually evolved into the story\Nbeing about one of the twins...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.65,0:01:39.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and the father\Nbeing the bad guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.08,0:01:42.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It went through a lot of drafts\Nof moving the story around...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.52,0:01:44.28,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and trying to get the right fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.36,0:01:47.48,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Though they populate\Na galaxy far, far away...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.56,0:01:52.19,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the characters of Star Wars embody\Nclassic archetypes from myth and legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.26,0:01:53.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,For luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.03,0:01:59.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas spent over two years\Ndeveloping the screenplay...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.37,0:02:01.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,carefully fitting the pieces together.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.41,0:02:03.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,As you write a screenplay,\Nyou sort of move characters around.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.01,0:02:06.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It's like a chess set. You have\Na certain set of main characters...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.78,0:02:09.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,you have secondary characters,\Nyou have sidekicks...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.38,0:02:12.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,you have villains\Nand you have henchmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.28,0:02:16.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You move these around to figure out\Nhow the story's gonna play itself out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.32,0:02:20.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,To help translate his characters from\Nthe page to three-dimensional life...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.83,0:02:23.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas hired\Nillustrator Ralph McQuarrie.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.56,0:02:28.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I found it very helpful,\Nin doing science fiction and fantasy...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.13,0:02:30.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to work with an illustrator...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.17,0:02:33.19,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to try to make concrete\Nwhat I have in my head...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.27,0:02:35.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so I don't have to spend\Na huge amount of time...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.84,0:02:38.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,describing\Nevery little minute detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.28,0:02:41.37,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I can just simply do a picture of it.\NAnd I sit down with Ralph...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.45,0:02:44.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and I tell him what the character is,\Nwhat it looks like...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.05,0:02:47.28,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and then he does a series\Nof sketches.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.35,0:02:49.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I take those sketches and say,\N''No, I want it more like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.02,0:02:52.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I want the eyes bigger.\NI want him smaller.''
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.42,0:02:53.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Sometimes completely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.93,0:02:57.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,No character represents\Na more primal archetype...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.36,0:03:00.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,than the hero of Star Wars,\NLuke Skywalker.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.43,0:03:05.73,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There is no particular character\Nin mythology or in stories...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.50,0:03:08.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that connect directly\Nwith Luke Skywalker.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.77,0:03:13.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Luke Skywalker is a hero,\Nand it's more generic...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.21,0:03:15.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,more of a motif\Nthat comes out of the various books...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.95,0:03:18.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,written about mythology\Nand fairy tales...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.02,0:03:21.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,such as Joseph Campbell's\NHero with a Thousand Faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.65,0:03:23.99,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Luke Skywalker's a tough character...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.06,0:03:27.18,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because by the nature\Nof that type of character...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.26,0:03:28.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,they have to be an everyman.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.89,0:03:32.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They have to be the person\Nthat we, the audience, relate to.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.36,0:03:34.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He was the person\Nthat we went on this journey with.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.57,0:03:36.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The dashing figure of Luke Skywalker...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.00,0:03:41.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,was destined to capture the imagination\Nof a generation of filmgoers...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.27,0:03:45.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but would he have been as popular had he\Nbeen played by, perhaps, Kenny Baker?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.84,0:03:48.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There was a point where Luke Skywalker\Nwas gonna be a midget...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.01,0:03:51.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and all the people on the farm\Nand everything--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.45,0:03:53.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the aunt and the uncle\Nand that whole group--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.99,0:03:55.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,were gonna be little people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.59,0:03:57.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That boy is our last hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.32,0:04:00.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,No, there is another.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.96,0:04:03.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was always about these twins\Nand their father.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.03,0:04:06.69,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That was the only thing that's been\Nconstant through the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.76,0:04:11.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And at some point I took the female twin\Nand made her the hero...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.24,0:04:13.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and then, eventually, I shifted it\Naround to the male character.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.84,0:04:16.90,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- I'm not going anywhere.\N- They're gonna execute her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.98,0:04:20.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You said you didn't want to just wait\Nto be captured. Now you want to stay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.08,0:04:23.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Marching into the detention area\Nis not what I had in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.25,0:04:25.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- But they're gonna kill her.\N- Better her than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.88,0:04:29.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,One of the ways of telling a story\Nis to have two main characters...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.45,0:04:32.62,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that are exactly the opposite\Nfrom each other so that they contrast.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.69,0:04:36.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I had Luke, who was\Nthe idealistic, naive farm boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.90,0:04:38.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,who was going out\Ninto the world--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.83,0:04:41.99,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,a little frightened to do that--\Ntake on the responsibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.07,0:04:45.26,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We had the old man, who was the guide\Nand the nurturing person...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.34,0:04:47.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,who was sending him off\Nand giving him advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.81,0:04:51.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You must learn the ways of the Force\Nif you're to come with me to Alderaan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.24,0:04:53.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Alderaan?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.38,0:04:56.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And then you usually\Nhave the sidekick...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.65,0:05:00.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,whose morals and everything else\Nare very opposite of the hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.19,0:05:02.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And so they kind of disagree\Non things, and in this case...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.99,0:05:07.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,one of the main themes is compassion\Nand helping one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.23,0:05:10.19,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Selflessness as opposed to selfishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.86,0:05:12.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So I have one character\Nwho's very selfless...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.40,0:05:14.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'm Luke Skywalker.\NI'm here to rescue you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.03,0:05:16.59,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and another who's very selfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.67,0:05:20.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I ain't in this for your revolution,\Nand I'm not in it for you, Princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.07,0:05:22.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I expect to be well paid.\NI'm in it for the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.67,0:05:25.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I put them together so they're always\Ncontrasting their points of view...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.94,0:05:27.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,on the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.55,0:05:32.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Han Solo is that character that\Nwe always wished we could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.62,0:05:34.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I think most of us\Nfelt like Luke Skywalker...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.79,0:05:37.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but we would've\Nloved to have been Han Solo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.16,0:05:39.62,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas originally envisioned Han Solo...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.69,0:05:42.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,as a huge green-skinned monster\Nwith large gills.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.93,0:05:46.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Raised by Wookiees, Solo had\Nbefriended Chewbacca at an early age...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.93,0:05:49.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and together,\Nthey had become space pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.50,0:05:51.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Han Solo was meant\Nto be a very nefarious character.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.00,0:05:56.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He did start out as a monster\Nor strange alien character.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.91,0:05:59.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I finally settled on him\Nbeing human...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.14,0:06:01.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so that there'd be more relationship\Nbetween the three of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.61,0:06:05.98,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That's where Chewbacca came in\Nas the alien sidekick.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.05,0:06:10.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,While several Star Wars characters\Nare drawn from myth and legend...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.12,0:06:12.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Han Solo's sidekick, Chewbacca...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.46,0:06:15.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,was inspired\Nby a more personal relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.29,0:06:18.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,My original inspiration for Chewbacca\Nwas my dog, Indiana.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.90,0:06:22.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,She was the one that sat there with me\Nas I was writing the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.20,0:06:24.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,She'd ride in the car with me\Nand be my copilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.04,0:06:28.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,When she'd sit in the car,\Nshe would be as tall as I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.24,0:06:30.73,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,She was an Alaskan malamute.\NShe was very big.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.81,0:06:32.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I thought that was a funny image.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.81,0:06:35.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,As I was looking for\Nan alien copilot for Han Solo...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.65,0:06:38.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I immediately thought of Indiana.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.08,0:06:42.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We had an old\N'30s illustration showing...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.22,0:06:45.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,a hairy, ape-like creature\Nthat George kinda liked.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.42,0:06:48.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I said, ''Well, let's make it more\Nlike a squirrel face or cat face. ''
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.79,0:06:50.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We tried to get something\Nthat was generic...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.93,0:06:53.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but not specific\Nto any animal breed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.83,0:06:57.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We started out with the idea of him\Nlooking sort of like a lemur.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.97,0:07:02.43,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Then I did one creature that\Nhad breasts down the front of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.51,0:07:05.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I removed the breasts\Nbecause it wasn't to be a female.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.94,0:07:09.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I put a bandolier on there\Nand gave him a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.01,0:07:13.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,As in almost every aspect\Nof the filmmaking process...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.42,0:07:16.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,creating the characters of Star Wars\Nwas a collaborative effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.85,0:07:19.12,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I come up with an idea in my head...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.19,0:07:21.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,of what I want a character,\Nalien or set to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.89,0:07:26.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Then I work with the designers\Nto take what I'm thinking about...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.03,0:07:29.19,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and make it concrete\Nonto a drawing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.27,0:07:32.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- I got him!\N- Great, kid. Don't get cocky.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.17,0:07:35.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Then I have to take that drawing and\Nturn it over to the art department...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.04,0:07:38.91,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,or the prop department\N{\r原文字幕}or the makeup department...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.98,0:07:40.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and they have to then translate that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.05,0:07:45.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,into a real\Nmechanical, plastic and fur reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.46,0:07:55.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We didn't really have the ability to\Ndo animated characters at that point...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.83,0:07:57.73,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so I made the decision,\Nwith Chewbacca...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.80,0:08:00.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that it would be a large man in a suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.07,0:08:05.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They said it was hairy and big,\Nand that was all that they said.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.24,0:08:08.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We arrive up there,\Nlooked around...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.71,0:08:12.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and there is Ralph McQuarrie's drawing\Nof a Neanderthal man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.58,0:08:17.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But the difference was\NRalph had put Bermuda shorts...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.42,0:08:21.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and a vest on Chewie.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.86,0:08:25.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I had no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.59,0:08:27.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?\NTrust him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.09,0:08:30.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,To make Chewbacca's\Nfacial expressions believable...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.03,0:08:34.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas turned to one of\Nthe few experts in the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.17,0:08:38.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I was working with Stuart Freeborn,\Nwho did the apes on 2001 .
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.10,0:08:41.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I thought it was a fantastic job he did,\Nand since we had this Wookiee...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.51,0:08:46.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I said, ''We'll use the same mechanics\Nthey used in 2001 to create the apes. ''
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.01,0:08:48.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,3 56, take four.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.61,0:08:53.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So he tried to take\Nwhat Ralph had drawn and interpret it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.15,0:08:55.12,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to use Peter Mayhew.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.19,0:08:58.68,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And he is a certain structure.\NHe has a certain way of walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.76,0:09:00.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He has certain eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.56,0:09:04.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Taking his actual skeletal structure\Nand turning that into a costume...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.93,0:09:08.83,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and a face that mechanically\Nwould work changes the design.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.90,0:09:11.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Just the nature\Nof the reality of it changes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.27,0:09:14.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Whenever you have a design concept\Nand you put it into reality...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.87,0:09:17.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,most of the time,\Nbut especially in the early years...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.81,0:09:19.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,it would change everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.11,0:09:22.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Now, with digital technology, it's\Nmuch easier to conceive of something...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.95,0:09:25.68,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,design something\Nand have it come out just that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.75,0:09:27.62,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But in the old days,\Nthat didn't happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.05,0:09:31.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We seem to be made to suffer.\NIt's our lot in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.42,0:09:35.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,One of the movies that inspired me\Nin the beginning of Star Wars...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.16,0:09:36.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,was Akira Kurosawa's Hidden Fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.96,0:09:43.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It's about two peasants who are at\Nthe lowest social level in feudalJapan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.18,0:09:55.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Traveling with a general\Nand a princess--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.75,0:09:57.68,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,very, very aristocratic people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.86,0:10:06.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So the story is told\Nfrom their point of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.39,0:10:10.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It's the lowest social category\Nwatching this adventure...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.86,0:10:14.73,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that is taking place on the grandest\Nlevel of international diplomacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.47,0:10:18.26,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They're designed as a kind\Nof Mutt and Jeff...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.34,0:10:22.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Abbott and Costello, Laurel and Hardy\Ncomic relief to the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.94,0:10:25.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I've just about had enough of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.24,0:10:27.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Go that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.48,0:10:30.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You'll be malfunctioning within a day,\Nyou nearsighted scrap pile.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.08,0:10:33.05,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And don't let me catch you\Nfollowing me, begging for help...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.12,0:10:34.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because you won't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.72,0:10:39.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,To make the comic relief work,you must\Ncreate two very different characters...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.62,0:10:42.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so I made one a little astrodroid...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.23,0:10:44.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that had\Nno human resemblance at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.46,0:10:47.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and then the other one\Na more elegant translator droid...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.53,0:10:49.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that was more\Nanthropomorphic in nature...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.70,0:10:52.53,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and more programmed\Nto interface with human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.60,0:10:55.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I am C-3PO,\Nhuman-cyborg relations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.87,0:10:58.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,This is my counterpart, R2-D2.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.54,0:10:59.91,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.98,0:11:05.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I wanted a very elegant,\Nsophisticated design concept for 3PO...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.08,0:11:08.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because 3PO came from a more elegant,\Nsophisticated environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.92,0:11:12.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'm not much more than an interpreter\Nand not very good at telling stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.39,0:11:18.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The early concept of 3PO was inspired\Nby the robot in Metropolis.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.76,0:11:22.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,3PO was to look like\Nthe Metropolis robot, only a boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.90,0:11:27.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and I made an illustration showing 3PO\Nand R2 coming across the desert...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.24,0:11:30.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and you could see their space capsule\Nin the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.58,0:11:33.98,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,One of the very diffiicult things\Nabout creating 3PO...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.05,0:11:39.18,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,is that I needed to create a face\Nthat was absolutely neutral...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.92,0:11:43.48,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that I could then read into\Nwhatever emotion it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.55,0:11:45.99,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that was being put forth\Nin the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.06,0:11:50.05,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I had a sculptress come in\Nand do a series of heads...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.13,0:11:52.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to try to get to a head\Nthat was absolutely neutral...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.93,0:11:54.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and had no emotion on it\Nwhatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.87,0:11:57.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I wanted all the reactions...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.47,0:12:01.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to be from the environment\Nand the story around it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.27,0:12:03.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so that ifhe was happy you would read\Nhappiness into his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.04,0:12:06.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Ifhe was sad,\Nyou'd read sadness into his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.08,0:12:10.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And it wouldn't be distorted at all by\Nthe physical configuration ofhis face.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.68,0:12:13.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Don't call me a mindless philosopher,\Nyou overweight glob of grease.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.38,0:12:15.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Come out,\Nbefore somebody sees you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.22,0:12:18.59,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I also originally was\Ngonna make him...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.66,0:12:21.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,more like an oily\Nused car dealer or a salesman--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.49,0:12:24.43,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He was gonna be more like a salesman\Nwho was always trying to please...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.50,0:12:26.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and always saying the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.43,0:12:29.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,-Can you speak Bocce?\N-Of course. It's like a second language.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.03,0:12:32.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,-All right. Shut up. I'll take this one.\N-Shutting up, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.40,0:12:35.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But as Tony Daniels\Ncame into it--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.21,0:12:39.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He was a very good actor,\Nand he had this British accent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.61,0:12:43.48,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I fell in love with the accent. I tried\Nto use different kinds of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.55,0:12:48.28,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,I tried to use the used car dealer.\N{\r原文字幕}I tried to use the salesman.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.35,0:12:51.91,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,None of it worked, except for Tony\Nas this kind of fussy British butler.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.99,0:12:55.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The very first day on the set\Non Star Wars, we got there...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.29,0:12:57.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and they'd onlyjust managed\Nto finish the costume...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.73,0:12:59.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and I actually got dressed up...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.03,0:13:05.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and I had to say to the continuity girl,\N''Could you take a Polaroid, please...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.70,0:13:07.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and hold it up?''
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.61,0:13:12.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And through the little eyes, I looked\Nat a little Polaroid of myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.54,0:13:15.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and that's where I really learned\Ntotally what I looked like for the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.48,0:13:18.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,If I told you half the things\NI've heard about this Jabba the Hutt...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.92,0:13:20.65,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,you'd probably\Nshort-circuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.72,0:13:24.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We first met 3PO\Nas this total gold thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.99,0:13:27.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It's very dangerous to have\Na shiny thing on the set...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.46,0:13:30.59,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because it reflects everything, from\Nthe car driving out with the supplies...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.66,0:13:32.19,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to the tea lady to the nurse--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.26,0:13:36.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And also, George's world was full\Nof muck and gristle and grime...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.40,0:13:40.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and so 3PO is spattered like that,\Ntotally against his nature, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.64,0:13:43.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,This oil bath is going to feel so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.97,0:13:47.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I've got such a bad case of dust\Ncontamination I can barely move.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.41,0:13:50.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He always gets polished up at the end.\NThis started in Star Wars...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.21,0:13:52.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,as a kind of end-of-the-play,\Nwalk-down costume,you might say.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.88,0:13:55.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Always polished up brightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.12,0:14:01.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Part of the fun of 3PO\Nis he has no soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.56,0:14:04.05,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He's programmed to think\Na particular way and be compassionate...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.13,0:14:06.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but he doesn't\Nreally know what that means.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.13,0:14:09.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Chewie, take the professor in the back\Nand plug him into the hyperdrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.27,0:14:12.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Sometimes I just don't\Nunderstand human behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.64,0:14:16.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Sometimes he gets frustrated and\Nhas very human-like qualities...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.17,0:14:20.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but they don't have a central place\Nwhere he can think independently.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.08,0:14:23.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Darth Vader, on the other hand,\Nas he becomes more mechanical...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.75,0:14:27.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,he loses more and more ofhis ability\Nto even think like a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.43,0:14:36.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Originally, there was\Nthe good father/the bad father.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.03,0:14:42.23,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The good father was Anakin Starkiller,\Nand the bad villain was Darth Vader.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.30,0:14:46.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In writing the scripts, those\Ntwo characters switched around a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.24,0:14:51.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I went back and forth. Ultimately\Nthey merged into being one character.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.41,0:14:55.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Obi-Wan never told you\Nwhat happened to your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.75,0:14:57.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He told me enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.92,0:15:01.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He told me you killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.52,0:15:05.68,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I am your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.53,0:15:14.99,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The decision to combine the good\Nand evil fathers of ancient legend...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.07,0:15:17.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,created an unforgettable character...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.54,0:15:21.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,one further enhanced by his nature\Nas something between man and machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.94,0:15:26.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The idea that Darth Vader was\Nbecoming more machine than man...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.71,0:15:31.65,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,and that he was losing his soul and\N{\r原文字幕}that he was losing his humanness...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.45,0:15:34.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,was a main theme.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.15,0:15:38.05,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In the case of Darth Vader,\NLucas's initial design concept...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.12,0:15:40.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,evoked bedouin warriors\Nof the Arabian peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.99,0:15:43.62,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George came in\Nand described Darth Vader to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.69,0:15:46.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,as a figure that fluttered\Nin on the wind--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.46,0:15:49.23,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,a very dark, spooky character.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.30,0:15:53.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He might have a big helmet on,\Nlike a Japanese medieval warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.00,0:15:57.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,McQuarrie quickly realized the\Npractical realities of space travel...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.84,0:15:59.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,would affect his designs\Nfor the character.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.35,0:16:05.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,His solution would come to be one\Nof Darth Vader's most sinister traits.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.48,0:16:07.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He's gonna come\Nfrom one spacecraft...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.72,0:16:10.78,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and they're gonna\Nblow a hole in this tunnel...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.86,0:16:13.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and come into\Nthis other spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.79,0:16:15.78,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I started to get worried...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.86,0:16:20.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,about him having to cross this space\Nin a vacuum without a space suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.13,0:16:21.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So George reluctantly said...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.87,0:16:24.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''Go ahead and give him\Nsome sort ofbreathing mask. ''
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.87,0:16:29.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Like everything I was doing, we'd get\Nto a certain point and he'd say...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.11,0:16:32.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''Okay, that's fine.\NLet's go on to something else. ''
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.41,0:16:34.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We left Darth Vader\Nthe way I had it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.35,0:16:37.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and he got into the film pretty much\Nlike I had painted him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.19,0:16:45.68,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,What George Lucas has done--\Nthe same as Tolkien--
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.76,0:16:47.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,is he's created\Nmemorable characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.33,0:16:51.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You've taken\Nyour first step into a larger world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.16,0:16:56.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I thought he had reached something\Nvery powerful and primordial.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.67,0:16:57.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'm not afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.87,0:17:00.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.40,0:17:05.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You think of Star Wars today, some\N25 years after the original release...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.91,0:17:08.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and you sort of don't remember\Nthe special effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.15,0:17:12.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You remember the characters. It's the\Ncreation of Darth Vader and Han Solo...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.38,0:17:14.98,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and Yoda and Luke Skywalker\Nand Chewbacca.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.05,0:17:17.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It's the characters that remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.22,0:17:20.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Why, you stuck-up, half-witted...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.79,0:17:22.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,scruffy-looking nerf herder!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.06,0:17:26.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Who's scruffy-lookin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.60,0:17:28.90,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,To be fair,you have to start\Nwith George's genius...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.43,0:17:32.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,for understanding human nature\Nand film.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.00,0:17:34.99,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There's nothing for me here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.07,0:17:37.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I want to learn the ways of the Force\Nand become a Jedi like my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.41,0:17:41.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,These mythologies\Nhave stood the test of time...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.91,0:17:45.91,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and become beloved by audiences\Nbecause of the fact...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.98,0:17:50.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that they have such wonderfully created\Nand performed characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.15,0:17:52.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Great shot, kid!\NThat was one in a million!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.49,0:17:56.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Remember, the Force\Nwill be with you always.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.93,0:18:05.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Han, can you reach my lightsaber?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.14,0:18:10.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Can anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.18,0:18:17.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That's my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.62,0:18:24.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I thought that was\Na deer's ass in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.79,0:18:28.19,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Cut!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.49,0:18:31.89,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,Cheer them on, guys.\N{\r原文字幕}Cheer them on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.96,0:18:34.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Try and climb up,\Nget back down again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.60,0:18:37.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Beat the-- out of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.07,0:18:44.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.36,0:19:16.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He was your favorite baddie.\NHe was doable as a bad guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.56,0:19:18.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It either scares you or thrills you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.93,0:19:21.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I find your lack of faith disturbing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.13,0:19:25.43,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There was something chilling\Nabout that breathing noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.10,0:19:30.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Episode III, ultimately,\Nis the story about...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.17,0:19:32.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,how does Anakin Skywalker\Nbecome Darth Vader...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.61,0:19:35.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and I think that's the story\Neverybody has been waiting for.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.51,0:19:37.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,This is the beginning\Nof the end for Anakin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.82,0:19:42.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You don't know the power\Nof the dark side.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.09,0:19:53.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Part of the reason I went back\Nto tell the prequel...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.13,0:19:55.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,ofhow Anakin Skywalker\Nbecame Darth Vader...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.37,0:19:58.53,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,is that it's an interesting story,\Nand it's a fun story to tell...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.60,0:20:01.90,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because it is the story\Nofhow a good person turns bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.97,0:20:05.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He progresses\Nfrom being a bright, smart...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.74,0:20:07.68,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,loving, caring young boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.74,0:20:10.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to being an attentive,\Nhardworking...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.01,0:20:13.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but ambitious Padawan learner...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.78,0:20:17.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,who feels that\Nbecause he's better at being a Jedi...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.89,0:20:20.05,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and his Jedi skills\Nthan most of the otherJedi...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.59,0:20:23.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that he should progress\Nfurther and faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.46,0:20:26.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In some ways--\Na lot of ways--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.30,0:20:30.23,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'm really ahead of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.30,0:20:33.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And as he progressed, it was\Nhis inability to control his temper...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.87,0:20:37.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and his greed to control things\Nthat were his undoing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.05,0:20:47.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,His whole slide to the dark side\Nis quite carefully done...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.89,0:20:49.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and it comes\Nfrom very human things--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.92,0:20:53.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that he's in love\Nand that he's going to be a father...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.66,0:20:55.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and that he's jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.43,0:20:57.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NWe've all messed things up...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.00,0:21:01.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because we're young and naive\Nand not able to step back...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.16,0:21:03.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and go, ''Oh, no. It's okay. ''
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.97,0:21:08.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Put the ship down!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.14,0:21:10.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Don't let your personal feelings\Nget in the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.79,0:21:26.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The problem that Anakin has\Nin this whole thing is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.99,0:21:30.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,he has a hard time\Nletting go of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.09,0:21:32.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I don't want things to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.43,0:21:34.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But you can't stop the change.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.53,0:21:37.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,As he sought more and more power\Nto try to change people's fates...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.00,0:21:39.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so that they're the way\Nhe wants them...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.67,0:21:44.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that greed goes from trying\Nto save the one you love...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.68,0:21:47.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to realizing you can\Ncontrol the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.36,0:22:01.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There was this missing piece\Nnow of Episode III...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.53,0:22:05.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the key missing piece, which\Neverybody's always wanted to see...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.43,0:22:10.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,which is the return\Nof Anakin Skywalker in the suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.54,0:22:18.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The face, the design...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.41,0:22:22.78,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the early Ralph McQuarrie inspiration\Nis still there...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.85,0:22:25.68,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and we've tried\Nto remain faithful to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.35,0:22:28.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,As we looked\Nat the original helmet...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.65,0:22:31.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,we've noticed\Nthat it's not a symmetrical shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.56,0:22:34.62,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was an opportunity for us\Nto make it more symmetrical...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.96,0:22:37.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and that's what we're trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.13,0:22:46.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,This is the bit\Nwhere all the detail needs to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.70,0:22:49.23,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so we've spent a long time\Ngetting this side beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.31,0:22:53.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I scanned it into a machine,\Nand then I flipped it in the computer...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.64,0:22:55.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and now I'm just\Ncutting the right-hand side.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.75,0:22:59.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Hopefully, by end of day, we'll have\Nthe other half to put together and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.88,0:23:02.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That'll be the first time\Nwe've seen the symmetrical Darth Vader.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.52,0:23:08.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We've got the beginning of the helmet.\NThat's gonna go into a mold tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.29,0:23:10.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We've got the shoulders.\NWe're starting on the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.46,0:23:13.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,These pieces are gonna start coming\Ntogether and become Darth Vader...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.63,0:23:15.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but we still have to do the boxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.80,0:23:17.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We have to start doing fittings.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.30,0:23:20.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Originally, it starts out\Nas just this beige suit...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.04,0:23:24.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,which isn't\Nvery intimidating at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.21,0:23:28.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But I still got this sensation\Nof nostalgia...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.55,0:23:32.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that I wasn't aware\NI was gonna feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.48,0:23:37.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting for you, Obi-Wan.\NWe meet again at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.89,0:23:41.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They could'vejust put some really\Ntall guy in it and got away with it...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.96,0:23:44.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but I begged and pleaded,\Nand they were nice enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.96,0:23:47.12,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to build a Darth Vader suit\Nthat actually fit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.20,0:23:49.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,When we put this helmet\Non before...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.57,0:23:53.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,it just looked too thin in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.47,0:23:57.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I don't know if you can really see it.\NBut by adding a little pipe there...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.71,0:24:02.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and by adding a bit in there, it just\Nbuilds it out and it fills in the face.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.85,0:24:05.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And it's much more\Nwhat we're used to seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.58,0:24:08.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So it's really weird things like that\Nwe're just discovering all the time--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.72,0:24:11.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,things that we thought\Nwe'd be beyond by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.16,0:24:16.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Simultaneously,\Nwe had to create a sequence...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.56,0:24:19.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,where both Anakin and Obi-Wan\Nwere gonna fight with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.00,0:24:22.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,This is a really difficult thing.\NThis is best friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.83,0:24:25.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You know,\Nthis is a mentor and his teacher...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.74,0:24:27.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and their relationship falls apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.87,0:24:29.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Anakin allows this to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.94,0:24:34.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Obi-Wan seems always to have\Nbeen a little wary of this child...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.18,0:24:38.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and having made a promise\Nto his dying master, Qui-Gon...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.35,0:24:41.37,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,he promises to turn this wee kid\Ninto a Jedi and look after him...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.45,0:24:44.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,which he does, I think,\Nto the best of his ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.96,0:24:48.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In the sword fighting,\Nyou have to learn a thousand moves.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.36,0:24:50.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It's very hard,\Nand you have to memorize them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.53,0:24:53.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And you really have to memorize\Nthem well or you get hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.43,0:24:56.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Fingers?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.03,0:25:00.23,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The repetition of having to do\Neach sequence over and over again...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.30,0:25:04.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and trying to get it so that it is\Nas perfect as we could get it to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.31,0:25:05.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,was exhausting.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.94,0:25:09.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We have to do that one again.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.05,0:25:12.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Hard work, but really satisfying,\Nat the end of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.15,0:25:16.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The guys would get so into it...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.32,0:25:18.62,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and then one will make a mistake,\Nand-- boom-- break.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.69,0:25:21.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They would be fine--\Nlaughing, everything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.09,0:25:22.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Seconds later,\Nthey were back into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.79,0:25:25.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,This would go on\Nfor hours and hours every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.37,0:25:30.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Ewan has always\Nbeen a great sword fighter...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.23,0:25:33.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but Hayden is very athletic,\Nand he's also very good at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.40,0:25:35.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The difference in this particular one\Nis they have to fight each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.37,0:25:38.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So we got some very,\Nvery good performances there...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.71,0:25:42.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,working their routines through and\Ntrying to be better than the other guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.32,0:25:49.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And that leads into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.73,0:26:01.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They've done more layers\Nof the silicone...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.40,0:26:03.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and then we've done\Na fiberglass jacket around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.77,0:26:08.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We've then taken all of that off\Nso we could get the original shape out.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.44,0:26:12.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So we now have an empty shell, which\Nis going to be our Darth Vader helmet...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.84,0:26:17.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,which now Adam is about to start\Nlaying up in polyester--in fiberglass.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.29,0:27:07.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There you have\Nthe Darth Vader helmet.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.53,0:27:10.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And it looks fairly good.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.43,0:27:14.23,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I think that must be incredibly exciting\Nfor Hayden-- being Darth Vader.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.30,0:27:16.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Getting into Darth Vader--\Nthat's the cool part.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.77,0:27:19.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,One more fitting with Hayden\Nand then filming on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.98,0:27:21.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And it'll be just a memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.45,0:27:34.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Everyone on my crew wanted\Nto be involved in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.66,0:27:36.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The day we were on set with him,\Nand he came into shot...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.03,0:27:39.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and you saw him shining\Nas he went up...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.10,0:27:41.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,you just thought,\N''That is an amazing thing. ''
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.00,0:27:43.69,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Takes us back to the old days.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.48,0:28:16.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,A long time ago\Nin a galaxy far, far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.69,0:28:20.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The next chapter\Nin the Star Wars saga--
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.99,0:28:23.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Return of theJedi.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.33,0:28:30.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The battle between\Ngood and evil rages on.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.60,0:28:35.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Join the further adventures of...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.57,0:28:37.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Luke Skywalker...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.24,0:28:39.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Han Solo...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.61,0:28:42.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Princess Leia...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.68,0:28:45.48,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lando Calrissian...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.25,0:28:47.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Chewbacca...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.68,0:28:49.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,C-3PO and R2-D2...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.52,0:28:53.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and Darth Vader.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.97,0:29:06.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Ajourney to alien worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.30,0:29:09.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It's a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.27,0:29:12.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,A rebellion against oppression.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.01,0:29:18.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,An epic ofheroes and villains.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.18,0:29:21.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,An adventure as vast as the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.42,0:29:28.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Return of theJedi.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.62,0:29:32.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Coming to a selected theater\Nin your galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.27,0:30:04.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The pirate and romantic films of\Nthe '40s were an influence on Star Wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.21,0:30:07.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Errol Flynn kinds of movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.75,0:30:09.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Everything is of that genre...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.95,0:30:13.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,which is the fantasy,\Naction-adventure kinds of films...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.39,0:30:15.75,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,of that period of time in the cinema.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.82,0:30:16.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,For luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.13,0:30:21.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The whole premise of Star Wars\Nwas that it was a romantic fantasy...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.56,0:30:24.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,in the great romantic traditions\Nof mythology...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.73,0:30:26.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,you know, King Arthur--
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.57,0:30:29.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The romantic side of fighting...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.24,0:30:31.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,where there was chivalry and honor\Nand that sort of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.51,0:30:37.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So, in developing\Na group of peacekeepers...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.75,0:30:42.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,who were above everything and\Nhonorable and could make decisions...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.92,0:30:45.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and bring peace to the galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.89,0:30:49.91,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I needed a weapon that was\Nappropriate for those kinds ofJedi.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.99,0:30:52.43,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Your father wanted you to have this\Nwhen you were old enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.06,0:30:55.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but your uncle wouldn't allow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.70,0:31:00.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- What is it?\N- Your father's lightsaber.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.80,0:31:02.53,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,This is the weapon of a Jedi knight.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.67,0:31:06.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Not as clumsy or random\Nas a blaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.51,0:31:09.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,An elegant weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.78,0:31:12.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,for a more civilized age.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.51,0:31:15.28,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was more a symbol\Nof a simpler time...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.35,0:31:20.12,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,of a time before the Empire had\Ntaken over, a time when honor ruled.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.19,0:31:23.78,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So, it was more of a symbol than it was\Nan actual weapon in the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.86,0:31:27.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Hokey religions and ancient weapons\Nare no match for a blaster at your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.56,0:31:30.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You don't believe\Nin the Force, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.30,0:31:33.43,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The original concept was that\NtheJedi would fight with swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.50,0:31:35.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Then I wanted to make it\Na futuristic kind of sword...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.04,0:31:38.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so I made it a lightsaber,\Nwhich is sort of a laser sword...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.04,0:31:42.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to give it\Nthat technology edge to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.72,0:31:51.48,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In an age of ray guns\Nand that sort of thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.55,0:31:53.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,it would deflect the rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.52,0:31:56.62,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Since the whole premise was that a Jedi\Nwas there to protect himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.69,0:31:59.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and not really be offensive,\Nbut be defensive...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.80,0:32:03.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that a laser sword in a world\Nof ray guns...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.63,0:32:05.73,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,would be\Na perfect defensive weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.91,0:32:20.78,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It started out as a kind of\NOriental form of swordplay...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.85,0:32:24.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,where there was a lot of honor involved\Nand a lot of skill and craft...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.35,0:32:28.12,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and higher spiritual meaning\Nto the sword fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.19,0:32:31.59,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So they were very simple.\NIn the beginning...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.66,0:32:33.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the first film, Episode IV...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.90,0:32:36.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,it was a fight between\Na very old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.60,0:32:40.69,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and a man who was only partially\Na man and mostly a mechanical being.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.77,0:32:43.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So it wasn't really\Nmuch of a sword fight at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.24,0:32:46.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,When I left, I was but a learner.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.17,0:32:47.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Now I am the master.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.88,0:32:49.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Only a master of evil, Darth.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.39,0:33:06.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The original lightsaber was actually\Nthe flash attachment to a 4-by-5 camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.39,0:33:10.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We took the round flash part off\Nand made it into a lightsaber.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.73,0:33:12.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George was adamant that these things...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.83,0:33:16.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,were really, really heavy,\Nthat we couldn't take a hand off.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.57,0:33:19.23,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We always had to have two.\NIt was like Excalibur.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.31,0:33:21.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was 40, 50 pounds of weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.28,0:33:23.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They were very powerful.\NThey had a lot of energy in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.95,0:33:28.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And so you worked with them\Nas if they were heavy...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.58,0:33:31.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because when\Nthey crashed together...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.45,0:33:33.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,they made these big\Nexplosions and all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.02,0:33:36.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,As we went on...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.29,0:33:39.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,we wanted to have the lightsaber fights\Nbecome faster and more intense...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.96,0:33:43.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,as Luke became more proficient\Nin the art of sword fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.97,0:33:48.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So, we very slowly started moving\Naway from the two-handed form...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.24,0:33:52.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,which is more Oriental, to sometimes\Nusing a one-handed form.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.71,0:33:54.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And it's progressed\Nfurther and further...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.71,0:33:57.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,into a more two-handed\Nand one-handed form.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.41,0:34:00.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Originally it was that you needed two\Nhands to hold onto this lightsaber...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.65,0:34:04.05,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because of the amount of energy\Nthat is being swung around.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.26,0:34:09.05,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You see? You can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.62,0:34:10.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I call it luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.89,0:34:13.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In my experience,\Nthere's no such thing as luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.56,0:34:19.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The effect of the lightsaber\Nwas basically a rotating pole...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.13,0:34:22.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that had movie screen material\Napplied to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.04,0:34:25.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so that it would reflect\Nits light source back...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.34,0:34:27.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,at many times the intensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.34,0:34:30.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The problem was that when you moved it\Nout of a certain area...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.61,0:34:32.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,it went from glowing\Nand looking great...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.68,0:34:34.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,tojust a rotating pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.82,0:34:37.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We'd rotate it with reflective tape\Nso it would flash...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.65,0:34:39.75,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and would create light\Non the actors.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.82,0:34:43.12,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That never worked. As soon as they hit\Neach other, they broke the lightsabers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.19,0:34:46.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So then we'djust use the sticks\Nwith the reflective material on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.86,0:34:49.23,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,As we moved on, we got more...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.90,0:34:51.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,proficient at actually\Ndoing sword fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.03,0:34:55.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We then used swords that didn't\Nhave the reflective material...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.64,0:35:00.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but we toned down the fact that we had\Nto shoot the light through the lens...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.08,0:35:02.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and a lot of other things\Nto try to make it...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.08,0:35:05.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so we could be more facile\Nin the way we shot these fights.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.41,0:35:08.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,1 1 8, BT, take two. A camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.38,0:35:10.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And action!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.95,0:35:14.65,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I thought it wouldjust be handled,\Nand they'd put in cartoon blades later.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.72,0:35:17.62,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But if you were sword fighting...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.69,0:35:19.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't know\Nwhen to stop your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.89,0:35:22.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You needed something to strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.94,0:35:33.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Every laser sword really\Nis part real and part animated.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.38,0:35:38.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We need the real pole\Nto tell us where the sword blade is.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.71,0:35:41.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And sometimes we'll use a short blade\Nbecause they're fighting so close...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.92,0:35:44.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that they would hit the set\Nand things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.29,0:35:45.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And sometimes we'd use no blade...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.95,0:35:48.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,'cause the blade would\Nturn on in the shot...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.36,0:35:51.05,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,or what they were doing\Nwas so complicated...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.13,0:35:53.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that we couldn't do it\Nwith swords themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.13,0:35:55.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And then we would\Nadd the sword in later.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.13,0:35:57.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But that takes a lot\Nof very careful tracking...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.57,0:35:59.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to figure out where\Nthe sword blade would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.87,0:36:02.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And even later on,\Nin the second and third one...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.04,0:36:06.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,when they decided that it was\Nmore trouble than it was worth...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.94,0:36:10.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to try and get on-set shots--\Nthey'djust do it all in post--
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.55,0:36:14.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,we still had part of a shaft...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.92,0:36:18.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,just so there would be\Nsomething to come up against.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.15,0:36:22.99,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That had a lot to do with the advances\Nin special effects technology...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.06,0:36:24.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,than it did anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.99,0:36:29.43,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,As we got more and more able\Nto do rotoscoping on these swords...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.50,0:36:31.83,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and we were using\Nmore advanced technology...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.90,0:36:33.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,it was easier for us\Nto follow the swords...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.14,0:36:37.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and copy them\Nand create laser swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.87,0:36:41.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You are beaten.\NIt is useless to resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.51,0:36:44.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Don't let yourself be destroyed\Nas Obi-Wan did.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.58,0:36:48.91,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Even though the lightsabers looked kinda\Nchintzy when we were shooting them...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.68,0:36:53.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,in postproduction they were able to\Ngive them the look they needed to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.72,0:36:55.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And, of course,\NBen Burtt's great sound effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.61,0:37:20.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The sound of the lightsaber was turned\Nover to Ben Burtt in the first film.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.35,0:37:24.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Ben worked\Nright from the very get-go...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.62,0:37:27.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,while I was\Nworking on the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.09,0:37:28.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I would tell him\NI needed a voice for R2.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.09,0:37:33.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I needed a voice\Nfor the breathing of Darth Vader.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.40,0:37:37.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'd need a sound for ray guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.80,0:37:44.53,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I need a sound for laser swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.88,0:37:56.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The very first sound I created\Nfor the film was the lightsaber.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.95,0:38:02.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I think what happened was I saw some of\Nthe Ralph McQuarrie artwork on the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.46,0:38:05.19,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was a picture of Luke fighting\Nat the end of the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.26,0:38:08.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They had these lightsabers. Immediately\Nsomething went off in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.93,0:38:11.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I had a feeling\Nfor what they would sound like.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.40,0:38:15.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In the booth where we projected films,\Nthose projectors made a hum.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.57,0:38:19.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They weren't running,just idling.\NThe motors would sit there with this...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.34,0:38:22.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,kind of magical,\Nmysterious humming sound...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.21,0:38:25.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that I thought was musical in a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.21,0:38:27.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I thought, ''That's probably what\Na lightsaber would sound like.''
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.85,0:38:29.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Your powers are weak, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.35,0:38:33.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You can't win, Darth.\NIf you strike me down...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.46,0:38:36.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I shall become more powerful\Nthan you can possibly imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.03,0:38:40.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And I was searching\Nfor some other element.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.40,0:38:43.26,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I had a tape recorder\Nwith a broken mike cable.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.33,0:38:45.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Actually the shielding had\Ncome off of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.33,0:38:48.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,When I walked past a television set\Nin my apartment...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.70,0:38:53.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,it picked up the hum from the picture\Ntube directly into the broken wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.11,0:38:58.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That made a buzz. I said, ''That's\Na great buzz. That sounds dangerous.''
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.15,0:39:02.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I recorded the buzz. Normally,\Na sound person doesn't want buzz or hum.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.38,0:39:04.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In this case, the buzz and the hum\Nwere the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.43,0:39:13.62,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Of course,\NI had to take that sound...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.70,0:39:18.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and make the ''pass-bys''and the swishes\Nof the sword out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.17,0:39:22.43,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He spent the better part of a year\Ntrying to create those sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.50,0:39:25.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The first time I put in\Nthe sounds of the lightsabers--
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.71,0:39:28.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,it was a temporary cut\Nof the film--
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.54,0:39:32.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and not much comment\Nwas made about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.48,0:39:36.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I have since learned that when\Nno comment is made, then it's fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.02,0:39:39.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That it passes the test.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.12,0:39:40.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.12,0:39:43.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Most impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.63,0:39:45.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Ultimately, the sound\Nfor the laser sword...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.86,0:39:48.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because we wanted something\Nwith a lot of energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.60,0:39:51.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,was a combination\Nof several different sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.10,0:39:53.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,From a swooshing vacuum cleaner...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.94,0:39:58.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to a kind of clash\Nwhen something hits dry ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.31,0:40:02.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We've modified since then,\Nas we get weapons that move faster...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.24,0:40:05.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and we get double-edged lightsabers\Nin some of the newer films.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.78,0:40:08.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But it's always based\Non that same recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.92,0:40:12.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There's nothing you could have done,\Nhad you been there.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.22,0:40:15.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You'd have been killed too...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.22,0:40:17.99,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and the droids would now be\Nin the hands of the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.79,0:40:21.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I want to come with you to Alderaan.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.53,0:40:24.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There's nothing for me here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.60,0:40:27.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I want to learn the ways of the Force\Nand become a Jedi like my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.70,0:40:30.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In every episode, from IV, Vand VI...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.74,0:40:34.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I kept improving\Nthe sword fighting...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.08,0:40:37.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because the assumption was\Nthat Luke was getting to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.25,0:40:40.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,a better fighter,\Nhe was learning more.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.38,0:40:42.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But at the same time...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.22,0:40:46.91,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,he still wasn't being trained as an\NoriginalJedi would have been trained.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.99,0:40:51.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,AJedi uses the Force\Nfor knowledge and defense...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.36,0:40:53.12,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,never for attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.19,0:40:55.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- But tell me why I can't--\N- No. There is no why.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.00,0:40:58.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Nothing more\Nwill I teach you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.73,0:41:01.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In Empire Strikes Back,\Nit's the first time...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.17,0:41:06.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that the antagonist and protagonist\Nactually fight each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.27,0:41:08.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So, it is a very big fight...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.04,0:41:12.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and Luke now has become\Nproficient enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.68,0:41:14.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to be able to face Darth Vader.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.68,0:41:17.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So, it's a slightly\None-sided sword fight...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.82,0:41:21.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,where Vader has\Nthe advantage over him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.16,0:41:23.75,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Luke didn't know\Nthat Vader was his father...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.83,0:41:25.69,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,really for the fight part.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.76,0:41:28.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He thought he was fighting\Nhis bitter enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.60,0:41:30.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And so he was fighting\Nas hard as he could.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.43,0:41:32.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He thought he was fighting the man\Nwho killed his father...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.93,0:41:35.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,fighting the man\Nwho killed Obi-Wan Kenobi...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.10,0:41:38.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,fighting the man who personified evil\Nin the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.34,0:41:41.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And then as we go on\Ninto the next fight...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.41,0:41:44.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,it becomes more of\Nan equal confrontation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.41,0:41:48.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In the next one,\NReturn of theJedi...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.48,0:41:50.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,he knew he was\Nfighting his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.08,0:41:53.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I see you have constructed\Na new lightsaber.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.66,0:41:56.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He knew that the emperor\Nwas behind all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.29,0:41:58.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Your skills are complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.79,0:42:02.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And he knew that the issues he was\Ndealing with were much larger...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.13,0:42:03.83,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,than just the sword fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.90,0:42:08.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Indeed you are powerful,\Nas the emperor has foreseen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.34,0:42:12.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So that sword fight centered on\Nthe more emotional context...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.77,0:42:15.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the sword fight takes place in\Nthan the fighting itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.11,0:42:16.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.61,0:42:22.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That was the climax of the film.\NRather than having it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.28,0:42:27.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,a technological warfare,\Nblow up the Death Star kind of thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.59,0:42:30.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,it was really more of a personal fight\Nbetween a father and a son.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.51,0:42:55.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Then when we moved\Nto the prequel...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.28,0:42:58.25,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,where there wereJedi\Nin their full flower...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.32,0:43:02.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and fighting as they were in the past--\Nwell-trained Jedi--
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.46,0:43:05.19,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,we had to make the sword fights\Nmuch, much faster...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.26,0:43:09.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,much more sophisticated and much more\Naggressive in the way they're fought.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.07,0:43:13.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We continued that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.47,0:43:14.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Brave of you, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.10,0:43:18.37,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But I would have thought\Nyou had learned your lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.44,0:43:20.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I am a slow learner.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.14,0:43:21.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Anakin!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.51,0:43:26.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The fights become much more ferocious\Nthan the ones in Episodes IV, Vand VI.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.82,0:43:36.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Fought well you have,\Nmy old Padawan.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.49,0:43:38.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,This is just the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.60,0:43:50.90,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Each one builds on the other, because\Nthe fights become more personal...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.97,0:43:54.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,until we get to Episode III where it's\Na very personal form of fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.41,0:43:58.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In this one, they have to fight each\Nother, so there's this very long fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.98,0:44:06.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The difference between the characters\Nis that Obi-Wan has more experience...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.59,0:44:08.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but Anakin's more powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.03,0:44:11.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.80,0:44:17.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Thanks, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.27,0:44:19.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You know, I'm here today\Nas Luke Skywalker...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.63,0:44:22.90,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but I'm also here\Nto talk about Sprint.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.97,0:44:26.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,As you can see, you stand to save\Nup to 1 7 cents a month...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.11,0:44:27.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,over the more\Ndependable providers.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.17,0:45:15.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Luke Skywalker and Han Solo\Nrescued the princess...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.10,0:45:18.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,destroyed the Death Star,\Nbut their story didn't end there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.88,0:45:30.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Now the creators of\Nthe biggest smash hit of all time...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.65,0:45:33.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,bring you the next episode\Nin the Star Wars saga--
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.49,0:45:35.98,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The Empire Strikes Back.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.10,0:45:48.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The continuing story\Nof our band ofheroes...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.04,0:45:50.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Luke Skywalker...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.57,0:45:52.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Princess Leia...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.11,0:45:53.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Han Solo...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.51,0:45:54.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,C-3PO...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.91,0:45:56.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,R2-D2...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.45,0:45:58.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and Chewbacca.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.18,0:46:01.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And introducing\NLando Calrissian.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.45,0:46:03.68,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It's an epic of romance...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.23,0:46:14.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,ofheroes and villains.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.31,0:46:27.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They cross trackless voids\Nto unknown worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.05,0:46:40.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,A galactic odyssey against oppression.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.07,0:46:57.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,A big, new sprawling space adventure\Nin the Star Wars saga--
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.74,0:47:00.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The Empire Strikes Back.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.21,0:47:08.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Coming to your galaxy next summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.92,0:47:21.62,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'm Luke Skywalker.\NI'm here to rescue you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.26,0:47:29.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It is the most popular\Nspace adventure of all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.47,0:47:31.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''Exciting''is hardly\Nthe word I would choose.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.77,0:47:35.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It's one of the most groundbreaking\Nsagas in Hollywood history.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.37,0:47:37.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There'll be no one\Nto stop us this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.31,0:47:40.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It captured imaginations\Nwith an irresistible force...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.71,0:47:43.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You've taken your first step\Ninto a larger world.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.51,0:47:47.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and catapulted three young performers\Nto superstardom.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.42,0:47:50.48,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- I got him!\N- Great kid! Don't get cocky.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.92,0:47:54.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,My whole life was changed by\Nthe opportunities that came to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.52,0:47:56.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,through the success of Star Wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.26,0:48:01.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It really is a wonderful morality tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.83,0:48:03.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'll never turn to the dark side.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.63,0:48:06.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It's George's vision,\Nand he truly is...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.67,0:48:10.23,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,a visual man\Nin a profound way.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.61,0:48:13.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But the Star Wars trilogy...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.41,0:48:15.90,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,didn'tjust change\Nthe way we look at movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.98,0:48:18.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It changed the way\Nthat movies are made.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.71,0:48:21.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You must unlearn\Nwhat you have learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.92,0:48:24.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There are so many accomplishments\Nthat George has done...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.15,0:48:27.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that really have changed\Nthe business as we know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.96,0:48:29.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.59,0:48:32.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,What began as\Na galactic fairy tale...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.09,0:48:35.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,became a success story\Nbeyond one man's wildest dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.00,0:48:38.43,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The Force will be with you always.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.50,0:48:42.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I expected not to ever make a hit movie.\NThat wasn't my agenda.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.24,0:48:45.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I certainly didn't expect\NStar Wars to be this giant hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.51,0:48:52.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But it became\Nsuch a phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.61,0:49:21.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It's hard to remember a time\Nbefore Star Wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.55,0:49:27.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The world was different then.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.28,0:49:31.98,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There were no cell phones\Nor personal computers.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.69,0:49:35.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The Internet was years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.09,0:49:37.65,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Even home video\Nhad yet to catch on.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.13,0:49:43.19,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- The space race was over.\N- That's one small step for man.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.27,0:49:45.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Americans felt deeply mired\Nin the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.64,0:49:49.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was a time of economic inflation...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.94,0:49:52.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and rising oil prices...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.87,0:49:56.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and the nation had grown cynical\Nabout its heroes and its leaders.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.65,0:49:58.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'm not a crook.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.65,0:50:01.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In our country,\NWatergate tore us apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.88,0:50:04.25,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And then we had\Nthe Vietnam War on top of that...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.32,0:50:07.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,which was dividing the nation\Nlike nothing else had.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.82,0:50:12.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was a terrible decade of great\Nstorm and violence in our history.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.43,0:50:17.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,On the big screen, Hollywood's\Nview was equally grim.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.57,0:50:23.90,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The films of the early 1 970s\Nwere gritty and often downbeat...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.97,0:50:27.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,a reflection of America's\Nsocial and political upheaval.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.34,0:50:29.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Instead of old-fashioned heroes...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.61,0:50:34.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the screen was dominated by hard-nosed\Nantiheroes who broke all the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.52,0:50:39.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In the late '60s,\Nthe Warners, the Zanucks...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.96,0:50:42.69,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,all the people that started\Nthe studios in the first place...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.76,0:50:46.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,were retiring, and they were selling\Nthe studios to corporations.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.40,0:50:49.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They were beverage companies\Nand all kinds of other other businesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.73,0:50:53.43,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They didn't know at all\Nhow to run a movie studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.50,0:50:56.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,All they know is if the marketing\Ndepartment said people want this...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.24,0:50:57.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,then you make that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.24,0:50:58.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They started marketing pictures...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.64,0:51:01.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and studying the demographics\Nand all these kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.24,0:51:04.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They saw there was a market for films\Nmade by young people for young people...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.85,0:51:07.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,'cause the young person was becoming\Na bigger part of their market.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.45,0:51:12.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The studio system that lasted\Nfor decades had now collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.69,0:51:16.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And Hollywood executives, desperate\Nto connect with younger audiences...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.59,0:51:20.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,turned to film schools to find\Nthe next generation of moviemakers.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.56,0:51:24.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- Action.\N- It was in this atmosphere of change...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.10,0:51:26.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that gifted young directors\Nlike Francis Ford Coppola...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.24,0:51:28.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Brian De Palma...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.84,0:51:30.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Martin Scorsese...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.37,0:51:31.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and Steven Spielberg...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.01,0:51:34.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,brought a more personal\Nsensibility to the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.51,0:51:39.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was a state of confusion, and a lot\Nof filmmakers got to make projects...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.55,0:51:42.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that they ordinarily wouldn't\Nhave gotten to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.08,0:51:44.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And I got caught\Nright in the middle of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.29,0:51:46.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George was the kind of maverick\Nfrom Northern California...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.09,0:51:50.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,an independent filmmaker\Nwho was always extremely proud...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.96,0:51:55.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that he had very few\Nattachments to Hollywood.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.03,0:51:58.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Born in Modesto, California...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.13,0:52:01.23,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George Lucas grew up\Nreading adventure stories...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.50,0:52:04.53,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and watching movie serials\Non television.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.58,0:52:18.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But it wasn't until college that his own\Ndreams of filmmaking began to surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.62,0:52:22.25,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In 1 963, he left Modesto...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.32,0:52:25.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to attend film classes at the\NUniversity of Southern California.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.73,0:52:31.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I was teaching at USC,\Nand George was in one of the seminars.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.87,0:52:36.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We talked about some of his\Nearly attempts at filmmaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.14,0:52:39.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Right from the beginning...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.44,0:52:41.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George had a unique vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.08,0:52:45.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George was a guy\Nthat thought out of the box...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.15,0:52:49.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,as you can certainly see\Nby his student film THX-1 1 38.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.19,0:52:52.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,THX-1 1 38 4EB.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.42,0:52:54.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,THX-1 1 38 4EB.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.46,0:52:57.05,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,This is Authority.\NYou will stop where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.13,0:53:00.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He shot a film that was 20 minutes long.\NIt was supposed to be five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.93,0:53:02.90,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You're going for\Nthe emergency switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.96,0:53:06.46,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But he got a great deal of recognition\Nand opened the eyes of the professors...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.54,0:53:09.37,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that kids could do\Nsomething out of the box...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.44,0:53:11.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,beyond what the restrictions were.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.58,0:53:16.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas won acclaim\Nfor his technical skills...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.18,0:53:17.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and imagination\Nas a storyteller.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.18,0:53:23.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,His interest in mythology and philosophy\Ngave his work an added dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.95,0:53:27.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George's style was fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.46,0:53:29.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.13,0:53:33.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I don't care\Nwhat he was doing...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.50,0:53:39.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,it just looked more personal\Nthan some of the other work.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.07,0:53:42.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,After graduating from USC...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.37,0:53:46.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas joined his friend, Francis\NFord Coppola, in San Francisco...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.11,0:53:49.91,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,where in 1 969 Coppola\Nfounded American Zoetrope...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.98,0:53:51.91,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,an independent film company.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.85,0:53:56.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I came up with no intention\Nof actually becoming successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.18,0:53:58.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But I did have a very strong...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.79,0:54:01.48,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,feeling about being able\Nto be in control of my work...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.56,0:54:03.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and not having people\Ntamper with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.73,0:54:07.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In 1 97 1, Lucas directed\NTHX-1 1 38...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.96,0:54:10.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,a theatrical feature\Nbased on his student film.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.87,0:54:13.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But when Warner Brothers executives\Nsaw the finished product...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.97,0:54:16.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,they demanded Coppola return\Nthe $300,000...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.01,0:54:20.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the studio had advanced\Nto develop THX and other projects.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.34,0:54:26.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The fledgling company imploded,\Nand Lucas had to find work elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.02,0:54:29.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He decided to take matters\Ninto his own hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.58,0:54:32.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and start his own company,\NLucasfilm, Limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.29,0:54:36.59,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,For his first project\Nunder this new banner...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.66,0:54:38.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas chose American Graffiti...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.89,0:54:42.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,an affectionate look at teenage cruising\Nin the early 1 960s.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.46,0:54:45.99,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- I'm a ready teddy.\N- Well, get bent, turkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.57,0:54:50.83,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Produced by Universal Studios...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.91,0:54:53.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,it was loosely based\Non his own experiences...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.34,0:54:56.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,as a car enthusiast\Ngrowing up in Modesto.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.81,0:55:00.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I had gone from being extremely\Nexperimental and hard-edged...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.85,0:55:03.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and then really taking up a challenge\Nthat Francis gave me--
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.65,0:55:06.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''I bet you can't do\Njust a silly comedy.''
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.19,0:55:09.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,A warm and fuzzy comedy.\NI said, ''I'll try that.''
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.96,0:55:16.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The film was shot in just 28 days\Nfor under a million dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.63,0:55:20.62,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Coproducing was another\NUSC alumnus, Gary Kurtz.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.70,0:55:24.19,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Toward the end of the postproduction\Non American Graffiiti...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.27,0:55:28.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,we organized a screening at\Nthe Northpoint Cinema in San Francisco.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.55,0:55:33.48,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We felt the reaction\Nto the film was quite positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.55,0:55:37.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But Ned Tanen, from Universal,\Nwas very upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.72,0:55:40.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''You shouldn't be showing it\Nto an audience at this stage. ''
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.09,0:55:41.75,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We were flabbergasted.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.36,0:55:45.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,My first film they didn't understand and\Nmeddled with it after it was finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.96,0:55:47.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Same with my second film.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.63,0:55:50.26,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The corporate entity came in...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.33,0:55:52.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and jerry-rigged with it,\Ncut five minutes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.37,0:55:55.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But even before the release\Nof American Graffiti...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.64,0:55:59.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George Lucas's imagination\Nwas pointed at the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.91,0:56:04.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,All during this time,\Nhe was talking about the fact...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.91,0:56:09.25,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that he would like to do a Flash Gordon\Nkind of 1 930s space opera.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.32,0:56:11.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He started working on that in earnest.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.76,0:56:19.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,People said, ''Of all things to pick,\Nwhy in the world would you do that?''
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.00,0:56:24.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I said, ''It's fun to make films\Nfor young people.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.57,0:56:26.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It's a chance to\Nmake an impression on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.24,0:56:30.83,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I wanna do this.''
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.91,0:56:32.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,With his galactic fairy tale...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.67,0:56:35.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas hoped to reinvent\Na classic genre.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.54,0:56:38.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Among his influences...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.15,0:56:41.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,were the writings of scholar\Nand educatorJoseph Campbell...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.15,0:56:44.78,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,in which he explored the origins\Nof myth and world religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.85,0:56:47.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,When Lucas was writing\Nthe script of Star Wars...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.22,0:56:49.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,he was heavily interested\Nin Joseph Campbell.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.22,0:56:50.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,WhatJoseph Campbell\Nwas interested in...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.93,0:56:55.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,was to see the connections between\Nthe myths of different cultures...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.53,0:56:57.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to try to find out\Nwhat were the threads...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.03,0:57:00.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that tied all these very\Ndisparate cultures together.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.84,0:57:03.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I did research to try\Nto distill everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.27,0:57:04.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,down into motifs\Nthat would be universal.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.01,0:57:07.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I attribute most of the success\Nto the psychological underpinnings...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.91,0:57:09.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,which had been around\Nfor thousands of years...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.91,0:57:13.78,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and the people still react the same way\Nto the stories as they always have.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.85,0:57:16.37,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George is nothing\Nif not a good reporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.45,0:57:18.75,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And when he sets out\Nto do his work...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.82,0:57:22.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,he starts reporting from\Nthe best sources he can gather.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.96,0:57:25.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He brought Campbell\Ninto the process...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.83,0:57:28.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,of looking at his work\Non Star Wars...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.23,0:57:31.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and saying, ''Is this right?\NAm I getting it down?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.80,0:57:34.96,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,Is this the right emphasis?\N{\r原文字幕}Is this the right character?''
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.04,0:57:39.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Joseph Campbell said to me the best\Nstudent he ever had was George Lucas.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.74,0:57:41.83,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Like such epics as The Odyssey...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.71,0:57:43.91,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Beowulf...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.98,0:57:45.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and The Legend of King Arthur...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.88,0:57:49.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Star Wars drew from\Na shared pool of mythic archetypes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.18,0:57:54.12,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You have the youth who's on the\Nadventure that you can identify with.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.89,0:57:57.05,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You have the swashbuckler.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.76,0:57:59.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And you have the damsel.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.23,0:58:03.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,She may not have the reactions\Nthat are conventional...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.83,0:58:05.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,however she is in distress.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.97,0:58:11.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And you have the wise old man,\Nwho you go and you find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.74,0:58:14.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And you have\Nthe funnier characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.38,0:58:18.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I mean, it really adheres\Nstrictly to that form.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.65,0:58:23.05,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It's the traditional,\Nritualistic coming-of-age story.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.12,0:58:25.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,When I went into the mythological\Nside of what I wanted to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.99,0:58:29.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that's a key factor with heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.79,0:58:32.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,By the summer of 1 973...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.49,0:58:37.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George Lucas had created a treatment\Nthat he felt was ready to shop around.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.17,0:58:41.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Whether anyone would be interested,\Nthat was another story.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.68,0:58:52.48,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The most successful science fiction film\Nup to that point was 2001 .
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.55,0:58:56.48,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Successful then was that\Nit made about $2 4 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.55,0:58:59.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Most hit science fiction films\Nwould make about $ 1 6 million...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.65,0:59:02.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,which was the Planet of the Apes films,\Nand that sort of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.62,0:59:05.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But most science fiction films\Nwould make under $ 1 0 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.23,0:59:08.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There's no reason to think\Nthat it would do any different.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.10,0:59:12.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Star Wars was more\Nspace fantasy than science fiction...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.07,0:59:15.83,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but its galactic setting\Nmade it a tough sell in 1 973.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.90,0:59:19.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,When I was pitching the film,\Nall I had was a 1 4-page story treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.07,0:59:22.37,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was very vague.\NSaid it was kind of a 1 930s...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.44,0:59:24.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,action adventure,\NSaturday afternoon serial...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.45,0:59:28.25,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,based on the kind of Flash Gordon,\NBuck Rogers kind of comic book future.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.32,0:59:30.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And that's about all\Nthey knew about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.96,0:59:36.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In the '70s, science fiction\Nseemed to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.16,0:59:40.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,all about apocalyptic societies\Nand death and destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.23,0:59:45.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Not very inspiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.97,0:59:48.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We were fighting an uphill battle\Nwith a science fiction project.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.74,0:59:52.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George Lucas brought Star Wars\Nto Universal and United Artists.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.74,0:59:55.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Both studios passed\Non the project.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.24,0:59:58.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But the ambitious young filmmaker\Nwas secretly relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.88,1:00:02.98,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The last thing he wanted was to hand\Nhis dream project to the wrong people.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.05,1:00:05.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He didn't care\Nfor the studio system.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.15,1:00:10.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He used it because there was no other\Nway of doing what he needed to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.86,1:00:15.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Undaunted, Lucas presented\NStar Wars to Alan Ladd,Jr....
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.13,1:00:18.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the new head of creative affairs\Nat 20th Century Fox.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.93,1:00:23.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Ladd, a former producer, was able to\Nrecognize potential in the filmmaker...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.84,1:00:25.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,if not necessarily the film.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.87,1:00:28.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We had a meeting,\Nand George said...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.34,1:00:30.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''I've been thinking about\Nthis thing called Star Wars. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.05,1:00:33.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And he told me about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.21,1:00:35.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I said, ''That sounds terrific.''
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.92,1:00:40.18,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The technology part of the whole\Nthing was completely over my head.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.26,1:00:43.19,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But I just believed in him\Nand his genius.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.26,1:00:45.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I sort of recognized\Nfrom American Graffiti...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.89,1:00:49.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that he really was a genius,\Nso I just flew with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.00,1:00:52.26,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He understood what talent was.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.33,1:00:54.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He respected talent\Nand he was able to say...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.00,1:00:58.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''I think this guy's talented.\NI think we're gonna invest in him. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.14,1:01:00.23,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So, Alan Ladd,Jr. invested in me.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.31,1:01:03.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He did not invest in the movie.\NAnd it paid off.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.51,1:01:09.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In 1 973, Ladd's investment\Nin George Lucas provedjustified.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.95,1:01:13.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,American Graffiti was finally\Nreleased to rave reviews...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.62,1:01:16.25,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and became the third-highest\Ngrossing picture of the year.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.32,1:01:19.62,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It went on to earn more than\N$ 1 00 million worldwide.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.76,1:01:26.46,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,American Graffiti showed\Na very human center and a huge heart...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.53,1:01:28.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that George has always had.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.67,1:01:31.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I think that surprised\Na lot of people.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.01,1:01:34.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,With a preliminary deal\Nfor Star Wars in place...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.81,1:01:38.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas began writing\Nhis screenplay in 1 97 4.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.61,1:01:41.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It proved more ambitious\Nthan he had first imagined.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.98,1:01:46.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The filmmaker was able to\Ndistill his idea down to its essence--
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.42,1:01:49.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,an epic battle between\Na heroic Rebel Alliance...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.39,1:01:51.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and an evil Galactic Empire.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.07,1:02:02.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The chief villain, Darth Vader,\Nwas there practically from the start.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.37,1:02:05.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But it took time to come up with\NStar Wars's three main heroes--
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.04,1:02:08.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,a plucky young princess\Nnamed Leia Organa...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.38,1:02:12.18,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the fearless Corellian smuggler\Nknown as Han Solo...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.85,1:02:15.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and most important,\Nan idealistic farm boy...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.88,1:02:18.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,whose original name\Nwas Luke Starkiller.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.95,1:02:20.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Over the course ofhis adventure...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.99,1:02:22.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Luke trains to become\Na Jedi knight...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.99,1:02:26.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,deriving his power from a mystical\Nenergy known as ''the Force. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.63,1:02:31.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But along the way, the script\Nwent through radical changes.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.47,1:02:34.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,At one point, Luke was\Na 60-year-old general...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.24,1:02:38.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and Han Solo\Nhad green skin and gills.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.04,1:02:42.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Even the concept of the Force\Nhad yet to be fully realized.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.51,1:02:44.98,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Instead, there was\Nthe Kaiburr Crystal...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.05,1:02:47.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,a sort of galactic Holy Grail.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.88,1:02:52.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The concept of the Force was\Nan important one in the story.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.06,1:02:55.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The difficulty is...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.42,1:03:00.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,trying to create\Na religious-spiritual concept...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.46,1:03:04.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that works in a very simple way\Nwithout heavy exposition...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.50,1:03:08.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,or without it seeming\Nto pull down the story.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.10,1:03:11.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It got to be a very fat script,\Nabout 200 pages.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.17,1:03:13.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And the story\Nhad gotten away from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.21,1:03:16.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So, the only way I could\Ncope with it was to say...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.21,1:03:19.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''I'll take the first third-- the first\Nact-- and I'll make that into a movie.''
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.68,1:03:23.12,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But I'd written all this other stuff.\NI'd spent a year writing this story.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.18,1:03:27.18,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I said, ''I'm not gonna throw away\Ntwo thirds of my year...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.26,1:03:29.75,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and say,\N'This is all I can afford at this point.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.82,1:03:32.73,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,This is the only money I'm gonna get\Nis to do this one movie.'''
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.79,1:03:36.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I put it on the shelf.I said, ''By hook\Nor by crook, I will finish this movie. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.40,1:03:45.43,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But Star Wars\Nwouldn't be cheap.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.11,1:03:49.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,To get the Fox board of directors\Nto approve the necessary budget...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.64,1:03:51.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas needed\Nsomething dramatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.21,1:03:56.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He hired Ralph McQuarrie, a conceptual\Ndesign artist who had worked for Boeing.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.05,1:03:59.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'd seen some ofhis paintings.\NI thought he was brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.55,1:04:02.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I said, ''I want you to do some\Npaintings of these scenes I've done...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.96,1:04:06.05,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so that the studio can get a picture\Nof what I'm talking about.''
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.69,1:04:10.99,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,When I turned in the script, I had\Nabout five or six drawings to say...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.07,1:04:12.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''This is what it's gonna look like. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.53,1:04:16.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He had a concept\Nfor a big spectacular visual...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.47,1:04:19.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and it didn't come across\Nin the script.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.71,1:04:22.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So I tried to give it scale...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.54,1:04:24.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,juxtaposing the tiny little figures...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.91,1:04:28.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,with the great,\Nspectacular backgrounds.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.12,1:04:31.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George would say, ''Don't worry\Nabout how we're going to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.39,1:04:36.65,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Wejust want an impression of what the\Nscenes would look like on the screen. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.50,1:04:46.90,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,McQuarrie's artwork won over\Nthe Fox board of directors...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.97,1:04:50.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,who soon approved a budget\Nofjust over $8 million.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.64,1:04:53.73,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,With only the first part\Nofhis Star Wars saga being made...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.81,1:04:56.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas also needed to think\Nabout the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.54,1:05:00.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But his prior dealings with major\Nstudios had taught him to be cautious.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.48,1:05:03.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,When I made the deal\Nfor Star Wars...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.12,1:05:06.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,originally I made the deal before\NAmerican Graffiiti had even come out.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.59,1:05:09.75,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,'Cause Alan Ladd had seen American\NGraffiiti and said, ''I'll make a deal.''
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.82,1:05:11.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But he made a very--
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.46,1:05:14.43,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,you're gonna make X number\Nof dollars and this kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.50,1:05:16.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was like a one-page memo.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.57,1:05:21.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,When it came up to doing the contract\Nfor the film, about a year later...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.94,1:05:27.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I knew that what I really had to do\Nwas to protect the unwritten part--
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.58,1:05:29.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the other two parts of the script.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.81,1:05:31.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden,\NGraffiti comes out...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.81,1:05:34.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and it's a big huge, smash success.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.15,1:05:38.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So his agent came back\Nand said, ''Hey, look.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.52,1:05:41.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,This guy has made\Nthis huge successful movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.19,1:05:45.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Don't you think we should get more than\Na couple hundred thousand dollars...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.46,1:05:47.48,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,for writing, directing\Nand producing a movie?''
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.16,1:05:50.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I said, ''Yeah. I think\Nhe should get more. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.17,1:05:54.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I was very careful to say, ''I don't want\Nmore money. I don't want more points.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.57,1:05:56.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I don't want anything financial.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.40,1:05:59.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But I do want the right\Nto make these sequels.''
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.04,1:06:02.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I was working on the assumption\Nevery filmmaker works on...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.51,1:06:04.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,which is the film\Nwill be a disaster...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.51,1:06:07.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and that it won't be promoted\Nand it'll just die a horrible death.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.82,1:06:11.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And it'll be very hard to get\Nthese next two movies made.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.22,1:06:14.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George said, ''I'd like\Na big slice of the merchandising. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.79,1:06:22.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Up until that time, merchandising\Nhad been relatively unknown.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.73,1:06:25.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,When I took over the licensing,\NI simply said...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.20,1:06:28.36,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,''I'm gonna be able to make T-shirts.\N{\r原文字幕}I'm gonna be able to make posters...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.44,1:06:31.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and I'm gonna be able to sell this\Nmovie, even though the studio won't. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.84,1:06:36.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So, I managed to get control of pretty\Nmuch everything that was left over...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.11,1:06:38.37,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that the studio\Ndidn't really care about.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.82,1:06:43.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George was enormously farsighted,\Nand the studio wasn't...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.58,1:06:46.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because they didn't know\Nthat the world was changing.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.22,1:06:48.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George did know the world was changing.\NHe changed it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.16,1:06:55.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,With his Star Wars contract\Ncompleted...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.13,1:06:58.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George Lucas\Nnow needed a rebel force...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.03,1:07:01.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,up to the challenge\Nof production.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.84,1:07:04.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In the summer of 1 975...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.31,1:07:08.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,he founded the visual effects company\NIndustrial Light & Magic.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.58,1:07:12.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There was no special effects\Ncompanies in those days...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.08,1:07:15.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and the studios'special effects\Ndepartment had been disbanded.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.15,1:07:17.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Part of that was because\Nof the expense...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.65,1:07:20.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and part of it was\Nthat the American taste...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.72,1:07:23.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the culture had gone toward\Nvery realistic-looking films.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.43,1:07:27.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We approached the visual effects\Nas a grand experiment, saying...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.03,1:07:30.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''Can we do this with a lot of people\Nwho work on architectural models...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.00,1:07:34.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and in commercials and have never made\Nfeature films before?''
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.27,1:07:38.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We were kind oflike\Na weird kind of fraternity...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.11,1:07:41.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,of robotic photography nuts\Nor something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.71,1:07:45.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I mean, this was a big movie for Fox.\NWe were doing commercials.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.98,1:07:48.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We all dreamed\Nabout doing a feature...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.15,1:07:50.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and this was like\Nthe dream come true.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.15,1:07:53.05,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So, Star Wars came along\Natjust the perfect time for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.22,1:07:57.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We moved into a big empty\Nwarehouse in Van Nuys...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.73,1:08:01.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,right near the Van Nuys Airport\Nand basically started from scratch.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.56,1:08:05.46,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I mean, it was empty. In the early days,\Nyou used to park your car inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.53,1:08:09.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There was no camera equipment,\Nno rooms to speak of.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.07,1:08:13.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Supervising at ILM\Nwas John Dykstra...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.87,1:08:16.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,an effects cameraman who had worked\Nunder Douglas Trumbull...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.81,1:08:19.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,on films like Silent Running.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.28,1:08:23.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I was essentially to be responsible for\Ndoing the visual effects for the film.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.48,1:08:28.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We took the concept of motion control,\Nwhich is essentially an old concept...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.79,1:08:31.59,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,ofbeing able to duplicate camera motion\Nthrough more than one pass...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.66,1:08:33.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so that you can generate\Nmultiple elements of film...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.03,1:08:38.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and we made it production-savvy\Nby tying it into a computer...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.23,1:08:40.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,which was, at that point,\Ncustom-built microprocessors.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.74,1:08:43.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There were no PCs.\NYou didn't go buy a PC.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.37,1:08:45.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We built them from scratch.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.21,1:08:49.73,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,At the same time the camera system\Nwas being built...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.81,1:08:53.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,another team began constructing\Nmodel spaceships.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.81,1:08:58.75,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I was one of the early hires.\NThey had a small art department.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.99,1:09:04.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There were some concept models made\Nout of cardboard and model kit pieces.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.86,1:09:07.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There were some storyboards\Nand some concept illustrations...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.00,1:09:10.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,thatJoeJohnston had done.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.33,1:09:14.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There were some paintings\Nthat Ralph McQuarrie had done.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.47,1:09:19.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Everything came\Neither from my sketches...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.17,1:09:22.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,or Ralph's paintings and drawings...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.64,1:09:26.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and any input\Nthat George might have.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.31,1:09:29.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There wasn't a lot of\Noutside influences on Star Wars.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.33,1:09:46.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George wanted it to look like\Nyou could actually see the rivets...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.90,1:09:49.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so you could see the logic\Nofhow it was made.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.87,1:09:52.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I was originally hired\Nto work on the Death Star...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.57,1:09:54.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the 40 foot by--
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.21,1:09:59.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,What was it? 40-by-80 feet or\N40-by-60 feet or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.51,1:10:03.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Nobody wanted thejob, because you had\Nto spend a lot of time on your knees.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.15,1:10:07.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Everybody sort of cross-trained\Nand worked in different techniques.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.86,1:10:09.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That was different\Nthan the Hollywood system...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.92,1:10:12.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that had very strict union rules.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.46,1:10:15.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But there was no way this work\Ncould be done that way...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.23,1:10:18.46,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,or no way that the Hollywood unions\Ncould understand what we were doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.77,1:10:22.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,With preproduction\Ngaining momentum...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.07,1:10:25.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas next began the process\Nof casting his galactic opus.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.01,1:10:29.53,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He shared the audition stage\Nwith his friend, Brian De Palma...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.61,1:10:33.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,who was seeking actors\Nfor the Stephen King shocker Carrie.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.35,1:10:36.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We were both making these movies\Nand casting at the same time...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.52,1:10:38.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so we decided to combine\Nour efforts.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.69,1:10:42.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I've made movies with very young people\Nthat have no track record...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.56,1:10:44.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so I have to discover them.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.39,1:10:47.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Pick them and then test them\Nand go through them and have readings.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.00,1:10:52.83,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It takes a long time. I spent probably\Nsix or seven months casting Star Wars.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.00,1:10:57.46,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That's a long process to sit\Nin a little room and interview people.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.54,1:10:59.37,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And I interviewed\Nthousands of people.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.04,1:11:04.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In casting the male leads,\NLuke Starkiller and Han Solo...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.58,1:11:06.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas looked for\Nindividual screen presence...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.58,1:11:08.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,as well as chemistry\Nbetween performers.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.65,1:11:10.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Action.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.32,1:11:13.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It checks out again.\NThere's no mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.86,1:11:18.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- You can't find Organa Major?\N- I found it. It's just not there.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.86,1:11:20.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I found it.\NIt's just not there.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.03,1:11:23.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,What's left of it\Nis contaminated.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.46,1:11:25.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That's it there.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.37,1:11:27.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Look at those radiation readouts.\NIt's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.47,1:11:31.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,-I've never seen anything like it.\N-The Empire must have gotten here first.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.34,1:11:33.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The planet has been\Ncompletely blown away.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.58,1:11:36.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,For the pivotal role of Luke...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.38,1:11:40.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas needed an actor who could\Nproject both intelligence and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.48,1:11:43.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,She's part of the royal family.\NThey won't get anything out of her.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.05,1:11:45.75,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,She knows the power of mind control.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.15,1:11:49.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,She's part of the royal family.\NThey won't get any information from her.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.56,1:11:51.53,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,She knows the art of mind control.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.96,1:11:56.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Twenty-four-year-old Mark Hamill was\Na familiar face on television.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.03,1:12:02.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,A newcomer to films, his wholesome,\Neasygoing manner fit the part perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.20,1:12:05.37,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I can remember a line\Nfrom the screen test...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.44,1:12:07.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,which I don't think\Never will leave me.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.54,1:12:12.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Luke says, ''But we can't turn back.\NFear is their greatest defense.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.31,1:12:15.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I doubt the security is any greater\Nthan it was on Aquilae or Sullust...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.58,1:12:18.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and what there is is most likely\Ndirected towards a large-scale assault.''
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.09,1:12:21.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Fear is their greatest defense.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.22,1:12:24.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I doubt the security is much greater\Nthan on Aquilae or Sullust...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.22,1:12:27.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and what there is is most likely\Ndirected towards a large-scale assault.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.13,1:12:30.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I read that line and I thought,\N''Who talks like this?''
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.80,1:12:32.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So I just did it sincerely.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.53,1:12:35.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,How many more systems\Nmust get blown away...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.47,1:12:37.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,before you have no place to hide\Nand are forced to fight?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.77,1:12:39.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Don't you realize what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.44,1:12:43.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Kid, you take the glory\Nand the good intentions.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.31,1:12:45.28,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'll take the reward.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.21,1:12:48.98,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The role of Han Solo\Nneeded someone older...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.05,1:12:50.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,with a more cynical edge.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.82,1:12:53.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,What's that little droid carrying\Nthat's so blasted important?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.79,1:12:57.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,What's the little droid carrying\Nthat's so important?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.03,1:13:02.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Harrison Ford had worked\Nwith Lucas on American Graffiti.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.60,1:13:05.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But because the director\Ninitially only wanted new faces...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.83,1:13:07.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,he was not allowed to audition.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.87,1:13:10.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Do I have to sit up\Nto get in on the right?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.84,1:13:14.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Instead, he was brought in\Nto feed lines to the other actors.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.71,1:13:19.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I was given sides and asked if\NI would help read the other actors.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.48,1:13:23.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It became my task to explain to the\Nother actors who were coming along...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.05,1:13:27.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,just what it was that these sides...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.32,1:13:31.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,were meant to be about.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.09,1:13:33.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They're gonna follow us.\NThey'll destroy your hidden bases.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.79,1:13:35.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- They'll destroy the whole system.\N- I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.03,1:13:37.83,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They'll bring the Death Star too.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.73,1:13:41.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas may have been reluctant\Nto use Ford at first...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.77,1:13:45.26,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but the actor won him over by\Ngiving Han a mix of mercenary swagger...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.34,1:13:47.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and world-weariness.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.54,1:13:51.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Well, what was so clear was what the\Nidea was of the character relationships.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.68,1:13:54.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Mark was the callow youth,\NI was the smart-ass...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.95,1:13:58.65,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and we each had\Na clear section of turfto explore.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.65,1:14:01.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The planet's totally blown away.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.66,1:14:06.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It would've taken 1 ,000 ships with more\Nfirepower than I've ever seen to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.66,1:14:10.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,If the Empire had a new weapon\Nthat could do this, I'd know about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.66,1:14:12.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'd have heard something.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.67,1:14:14.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Well, you know about it now.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.67,1:14:17.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The enemy's on the move.\NWe haven't much time.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.17,1:14:20.83,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- I brought you here. Now what?\N- We've got to find the rebels.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.91,1:14:26.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- What we're carrying belongs to them.\N- Their bases are very well hidden, son.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.15,1:14:28.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,All the power of the Empire\Ncan't find 'em.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.62,1:14:30.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Do you know where they are?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.48,1:14:31.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,No. Not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.79,1:14:35.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'm not gonna take you on\Nan impossible chase across the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.39,1:14:37.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Virtually every young actress\Nin Hollywood...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.96,1:14:40.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,tried out for the part\Nof Princess Leia.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.36,1:14:43.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Although the character\Nwas the same age as Luke...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.36,1:14:45.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,as a leader of the rebellion\NLeia needed to project...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.03,1:14:48.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,a confidence beyond her years.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.10,1:14:52.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The plans and specifications\Nto a battle station...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.47,1:14:54.53,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,with enough firepower\Nto destroy an entire system.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.61,1:14:57.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Our only hope in destroying it\Nis to find its weakness...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.61,1:15:00.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,which we will determine\Nfrom the data I stored in R2.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.88,1:15:03.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Now, our only hope\Nin destroying it...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.38,1:15:05.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,is to find its weakness...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.39,1:15:07.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,which we'll do from the data\NI stored in R2.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.09,1:15:12.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Okay? Now, we've captured the plans\Nin a raid on the imperial shipyards.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.39,1:15:15.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But we fell under attack before\NI could get the data to safety...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.40,1:15:18.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so I hid it in R2\Nand sent him off.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.10,1:15:22.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,When R2 has been safely delivered\Nto my forces, you get your reward.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.04,1:15:24.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You have my guarantee.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.04,1:15:28.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,What's the little droid carrying\Nthat's so blasted important?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.38,1:15:31.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The plans and specifications...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.38,1:15:33.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to a battle station\Nwith enough firepower...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.88,1:15:35.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to destroy an entire system.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.15,1:15:39.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,One actress in particular...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.15,1:15:41.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,seemed tailor-made\Nto play a princess.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.49,1:15:45.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,As the daughter of actress Debbie\NReynolds and singer Eddie Fisher...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.36,1:15:49.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Carrie Fisher was the product\Nof Hollywood royalty.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.23,1:15:52.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,She had no trouble conveying the\Nself-assurance needed for Leia Organa.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.03,1:15:55.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I met with Brian De Palma\Nand George...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.17,1:15:57.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and Brian did all the talking...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.54,1:15:59.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because George didn't talk then.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.17,1:16:05.48,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There were incredible actresses my age\Nbeing considered for this role...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.55,1:16:07.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so I didn't think I would get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.12,1:16:11.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But our only hope is to destroy it\Nbefore it destroys us.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.95,1:16:15.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Hiding is useless now.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.22,1:16:18.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,With the Death Star, they'll continue\Nto go on destroying systems...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.49,1:16:20.43,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,until they've found us.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.49,1:16:23.43,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We have no alternative\Nbut to process the information...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.50,1:16:25.69,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and use it while there's still time.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.77,1:16:29.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I got it with the proviso\Nthat I went to a fat farm...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.47,1:16:32.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and that I lose 1 0 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.04,1:16:37.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I think they were hoping it was gonna\Ncome out five here and five here.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.91,1:16:41.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,My character was someone\Nwho was feisty and all of that...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.58,1:16:44.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but I felt myself\Nto be a bit of that too...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.59,1:16:48.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so it would have been unlikely that\NI would be cast as a shrinking violet.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.96,1:16:51.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He cast us to type, in a way.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.63,1:16:55.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas's decision to hire unknowns...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.13,1:16:58.19,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,went against the advice ofhis friend\NFrancis Ford Coppola...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.27,1:17:01.46,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,who had cast The Godfather\Nwith stage and screen stars.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.80,1:17:04.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,20th Century Fox\Nwas also concerned...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.81,1:17:06.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,about Lucas's choice of actors.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.44,1:17:11.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They came and said, ''These are the three\Nunknown people I want to go with. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.15,1:17:16.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I figured we'd gone down this far\Nin the road, he knows what he's doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.78,1:17:20.69,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'd be lying if I said\N''Oh, my God, Harrison's perfect...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.75,1:17:24.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Carrie is perfect,\Nand Mark is fantastic. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.46,1:17:28.05,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,No, I was very nervous\Nabout the cast.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.13,1:17:32.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,For the important role of\Naged Jedi master Obi-Wan Kenobi...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.37,1:17:35.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas recognized that\Nhe needed an established star.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.30,1:17:39.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Sir Alec Guinness was\Na veteran of over 40 films...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.67,1:17:41.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and had won an Oscar in 1 958...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.01,1:17:45.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,for his performance in\NThe Bridge on the River Kwai.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.35,1:17:49.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The knighted actor had\Nthe pedigree and the persona.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.12,1:17:51.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The Alec Guinness role...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.45,1:17:55.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,required a certain stability\Nand gravitas as a character...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.42,1:18:00.26,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,which meant we needed a very strong\Ncharacter actor to play that part.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.40,1:18:03.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Signing Guinness was a major coup.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.03,1:18:06.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But more casting\Nwould be done in London...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.60,1:18:08.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,where Star Wars\Nwould be principally produced.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.00,1:18:11.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Unlike Lucas's home base\Nof Northern California...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.01,1:18:15.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,London provided access to the kind of\Nmassive soundstages...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.41,1:18:18.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,needed for Star Wars's\Nambitious sets.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.25,1:18:22.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The location also gave Lucas access\Nto Britain's top production talents.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.09,1:18:32.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The character of Darth Vader demanded\Nsomeone of commanding physical stature.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.06,1:18:36.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,To fill Vader's boots...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.06,1:18:39.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas cast champion bodybuilder\NDavid Prowse...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.40,1:18:42.99,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,whose resume included roles\Nlike Frankenstein's creature...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.07,1:18:45.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,in Hammer's\Npopular horror movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.67,1:18:48.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,As Vader's evil accomplice\NGovernor Tarkin...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.94,1:18:51.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,another Hammer alumnus was cast--
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.24,1:18:53.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,63-year-old Peter Cushing.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.88,1:18:57.65,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Best known as the methodical\NProfessor Van Helsing in Dracula...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.72,1:18:59.65,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Cushing was the perfect choice...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.72,1:19:02.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to portray the Death Star's\Nicy chief administrator.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.86,1:19:08.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,For the part of Chewbacca, Han Solo's\Ntowering Wookiee copilot...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.00,1:19:13.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas and Kurtz had to look\Noutside normal casting channels.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.37,1:19:15.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But at seven feet, three inches tall...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.57,1:19:17.83,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,it was no stretch for Peter Mayhew...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.90,1:19:21.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,who had been working as an orderly\Nat a Yorkshire hospital.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.74,1:19:24.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I sat down\Non one of the sofas...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.55,1:19:26.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,waiting for George.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.02,1:19:29.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Door opened...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.02,1:19:34.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and George walked in\Nwith Gary behind him.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.02,1:19:36.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So naturally, what did I do?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.02,1:19:38.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'm raised in England.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.03,1:19:42.69,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Soon as someone comes in\Nthrough the door, I stand up.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.00,1:19:45.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George goes--
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.50,1:19:48.99,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Virtually turned to Gary and said...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.07,1:19:51.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''I think we've found him.''
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.77,1:19:56.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Finding the right performers to portray\Nrobots was even more of a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.74,1:20:00.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Production designers had constructed\Nan assortment of robots and androids...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.91,1:20:03.18,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to populate the Star Wars universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.92,1:20:06.18,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But it would take living,\Nbreathing actors...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.25,1:20:09.05,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to give personality\Nto the two main droids...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.12,1:20:10.28,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,C-3PO...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.36,1:20:11.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and R2-D2.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.96,1:20:13.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,To operate R2...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.03,1:20:18.90,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas needed a performer small in\Nstature, but with a big imagination.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.97,1:20:22.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Enter 3-foot-5-inch\Nstage comedian Kenny Baker.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.84,1:20:25.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They couldn't find anyone\Nthat would fit inside this robot...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.77,1:20:27.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to make it move.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.94,1:20:30.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They couldn't use kids\N'cause it was quite a heavy machine.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.78,1:20:32.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It weighed about 80 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.51,1:20:35.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'd had a lot of experience\Ninside costumes...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.68,1:20:40.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and inside cats and dogs\Nand goodness knows what else.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.29,1:20:43.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So when I got into the robot,\Nhe said, ''Look happy. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.29,1:20:45.28,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So I'd go--
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.73,1:20:50.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Inside, nobody could\Nsee my expressions, obviously.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.23,1:20:55.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But you have to do something\Nto get the feel of the thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.70,1:20:58.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Actor Anthony Daniels...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.71,1:21:01.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,not only had the slender build\Nneeded for C-3PO...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.71,1:21:04.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but training as a mime artist.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.11,1:21:06.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He'd been seeing people\Nevery five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.61,1:21:10.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I was there for a while and thinking,\N''Well, nearly time to go, I guess.''
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.65,1:21:13.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And then, kind of over\NGeorge's shoulder, I saw a painting...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.02,1:21:15.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and the most extraordinary\Nthing happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.02,1:21:19.12,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Itjust struck me, because I kind of\Nlooked at this face...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.83,1:21:22.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and the face looked back at me, and we\Nhad this extraordinary eye contact.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.03,1:21:25.69,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He's looking out of the picture\Nand seemed to be saying...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.37,1:21:28.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''Come. Come. Be with me.''
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.37,1:21:30.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The vulnerability in his face...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.51,1:21:33.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,made me want to help him.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.27,1:21:36.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Isn't that weird?\NHe just looks utterly vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.38,1:21:40.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That painting completely changed\Nmy attitude to the whole project.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.21,1:21:44.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Years later I was able to go\Nto Ralph McQuarrie and say...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.22,1:21:47.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''You realize this is all your fault.''
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.42,1:21:54.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In March 1 976,\Nwith casting completed...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.23,1:21:57.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George Lucas and company\Narrived in North Africa.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.67,1:22:02.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was a strange caravan of British\Nand American filmmakers...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.67,1:22:07.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,working in a French-speaking nation\Non a script few people believed in.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.11,1:22:13.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The overriding thing for me\Nat that stage was...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.21,1:22:17.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the amount of work that we had to do,\Nof stuff there was to achieve...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.52,1:22:21.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and we had grave doubts\Nabout getting it done in time.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.16,1:22:29.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But the trial by fire\Nhad yet to begin.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.10,1:22:31.53,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was now up to Lucas\Nto make his movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.43,1:22:34.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Just one day into filming...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.37,1:22:38.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the Sahara was pelted with its\Nfirst major rainfall in 50 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.87,1:22:42.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We were going out there\Nto shoot on the salt flat.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.34,1:22:45.90,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I came out in the morning and the rain\Nwas going horizontally down the street.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.65,1:22:48.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I thought, ''My God--''
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.65,1:22:51.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I called a rest day on the crew,\Ntold them to go back to bed...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.79,1:22:54.48,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because there was no way\Nwe were gonna shoot on that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.23,1:23:01.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The first two weeks of shooting,\Nwe'd run into a lot of weather problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.16,1:23:04.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The sets had blown down,\NI didn't get everything shot.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.36,1:23:08.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was a disaster. At that point\NI was pretty depressed, saying...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.24,1:23:12.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''I've got myself in way over my head.\NI don't know what I'm gonna do.''
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.71,1:23:15.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You must do what you feel\Nis right, of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.88,1:23:21.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,With temperatures topping\N1 00 degrees by midmorning...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.15,1:23:24.28,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Tunisia was anything\Nbut fun in the sun.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.05,1:23:27.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Baking for hours\Nin heavy costume...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.69,1:23:30.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,even the film's stunt coordinator,\NPeter Diamond...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.39,1:23:32.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,found the conditions\Nphysically exhausting.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.03,1:23:37.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I was the only stuntperson\Non the picture in Tunisia.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.36,1:23:40.46,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I became a Tusken Raider,\Nor a Sandperson.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.04,1:23:45.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'm not a sun merchant.\NI don't like the sun. I just burn.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.94,1:23:48.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So I just died\Nwith the heat of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.11,1:23:50.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I couldn't stand it anymore,\Nit was so hot.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.38,1:23:54.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There were so many problems.\NItjust was not a good location.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.68,1:23:58.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We seem to be made to suffer.\NIt's our lot in life.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.32,1:24:01.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,C-3PO was finally...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.89,1:24:04.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,put together\Nfor the very first time...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.42,1:24:06.59,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the day before\Nwe started shooting.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.86,1:24:10.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,R2-D2 didn't really\Nfunction that well.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.83,1:24:13.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He could run along\Nin the three-legged position...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.40,1:24:16.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but he couldn't turn his head\Nat the same time.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.94,1:24:19.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There were wires everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.27,1:24:21.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The head was on a track\Nofball bearings.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.88,1:24:26.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I used to grab whatever I could and turn\Nit physically that way and that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.18,1:24:27.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Not very far.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.18,1:24:32.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,If I went too far the wires\Nwould go around my neck.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.09,1:24:34.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Then they'd say, ''Cut.!\NRight, break for lunch. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.56,1:24:37.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And everybody'djust\Nwalk away and leave me.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.96,1:24:40.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Then they'd remember me eventually.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.79,1:24:42.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That happened many times.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.43,1:24:45.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was bad enough putting\Non the costume for the first time...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.03,1:24:49.26,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and within two paces the left leg\Nhad shattered down...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.34,1:24:52.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,onto the plastic of the left foot...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.34,1:24:55.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and was gently\Nbut forcibly and persistently...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.28,1:24:56.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,knifing it...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.31,1:25:01.18,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,into the soft part of my foot.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.25,1:25:05.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So we took it off,and I limped\Nto the set with one foot.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.15,1:25:09.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was then I began to panic\Nabout the days to come.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.16,1:25:16.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,As the actors and crew began to grumble\Nabout the adverse conditions...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.23,1:25:20.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,it was Sir Alec Guinness who served\Nas a role model of professionalism.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.93,1:25:24.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was, for me, fascinating\Nto watch Alec Guinness.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.17,1:25:27.26,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He was always prepared,\Nalways professional...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.34,1:25:29.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,always very kind to the other actors.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.28,1:25:33.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He had a very clear head\Nabout how to serve the story.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.18,1:25:37.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He was the person who sort of\Nbrought it some legitimacy.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.38,1:25:39.68,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I asked him\Nwhy he wanted to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.85,1:25:42.69,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He loved the idea\Nof playing a mentor or a wizard...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.76,1:25:44.69,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,in a morality play...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.76,1:25:47.25,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,where good and evil\Nare so clearly defined.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.13,1:25:49.62,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Action!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.87,1:25:55.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- How long have you had these droids?\N- Three or four seasons.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.44,1:25:57.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They're up for sale if you want them.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.94,1:25:59.37,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Let me see your identification.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.44,1:26:01.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You don't need to see\Nhis identification.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.44,1:26:04.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I don't need to see\Nyour identification.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.44,1:26:06.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,These aren't the droids\Nyou're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.95,1:26:08.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,These aren't the droids\Nwe're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.95,1:26:11.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He can go about his business.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.22,1:26:13.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You can go about your business.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.82,1:26:15.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Move along.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.26,1:26:20.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas, meanwhile...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.99,1:26:22.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,was up to his neck\Nin malfunctioning props...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.36,1:26:25.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,electronic breakdowns...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.40,1:26:27.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and other production woes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.37,1:26:32.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Star Wars was already\Nstruggling to stay on schedule.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.81,1:26:36.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The only silver lining\Nwas that after Tunisia...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.18,1:26:39.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the production would be moving to\Na more controlled environment--
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.18,1:26:41.65,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Elstree Studios outside London.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.12,1:26:46.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The stages at Elstree were among\Nthe largest in the world...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.49,1:26:49.65,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and the sets, now finished\Nafter months of construction...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.72,1:26:51.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,werejust as impressive.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.79,1:26:55.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,For the first time,\Nthe entire Star Wars cast was together.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.26,1:26:59.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That was almost like\Na whole separate movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.43,1:27:01.53,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was like getting\Na whole, fresh start.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.60,1:27:03.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And it was all new, really.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.47,1:27:07.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We were all\Nvery different ages.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.57,1:27:09.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I was 1 9, Harrison was 33.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.94,1:27:12.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He was sort of\Nthe big man on campus.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.91,1:27:17.18,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Meeting him,you sort of felt,\N''Well, he'll be a movie star. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.05,1:27:21.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Costumes, makeup,\Nrobots and aliens...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.22,1:27:23.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,were all ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.92,1:27:29.59,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I put that mask on\Nand Chewie transformed me.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.66,1:27:33.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I transformed.\NThe attitude was different.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.17,1:27:35.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The walk was different.\NChewie turned on.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.04,1:27:39.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Do the scenes, come back,\Ntake the mask off...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.91,1:27:41.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Peter was back.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.14,1:27:44.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Action.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.54,1:27:46.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That old man's mad.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.65,1:27:48.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You said it, Chewie.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.65,1:27:51.28,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Boy, where did you\Ndig up that old fossil?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.35,1:27:54.68,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- Ben is a great man.\N- Great at getting us into trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.75,1:27:56.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I didn't hear you give any ideas.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.02,1:27:58.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Cut.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.50,1:28:04.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But working\Nat Elstree Studios...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.40,1:28:07.26,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,didn't mean the production\Nwas free from problems...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.33,1:28:09.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,or strict British union regulations.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.30,1:28:12.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,At 5:30 we had to stop...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.84,1:28:15.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,unless we were\Nin the middle of a shot.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.21,1:28:20.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I could ask the crew\Nfor an extra 1 5 minutes...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.85,1:28:22.78,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but they always voted me down.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.45,1:28:26.75,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Not to put down the British crew, but\Nthere was an attitude of''What's this?''
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.42,1:28:30.05,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It didn't help that most\Nof the crew thought Star Wars...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.12,1:28:32.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,was just a children's film.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.13,1:28:36.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,At times even the actors were\Nhard-pressed to take the work seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.90,1:28:39.19,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Didn't think it was gonna be any good.\NAt least I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.27,1:28:41.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I thought, ''This is a bit strange.''
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.53,1:28:43.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I can remember\Nthis lighting man--
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.47,1:28:47.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He said, ''What is all this about?\NIt's a load of rubbish. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.01,1:28:52.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And we all thought the same at\Nthe time-- ''Yeah, it's a bit strange.''
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.88,1:28:54.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Action!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.21,1:28:59.98,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was a princess with her hair\Nin weird buns on the side...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.05,1:29:03.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and a giant in a monkey suit\Nor something.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.92,1:29:06.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I mean,\Nit was very, very weird.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.66,1:29:09.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,No more adventures!\NI'm not getting involved!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.50,1:29:12.99,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Don't you call me a mindless philosopher\Nyou overweight glob of grease!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.07,1:29:14.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Bang!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.77,1:29:17.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'm going to regret this.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.67,1:29:19.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was tough dialogue to say.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.61,1:29:24.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So I got, ''Governor Tarkin, I thought\NI recognized your foul stench. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.61,1:29:28.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Which, I don't know about you,\Nbut I'm always talking like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.08,1:29:31.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Governor Tarkin.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.65,1:29:34.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I should have expected to find you\Nholding Vader's leash.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.62,1:29:37.99,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I recognized your foul stench\Nwhen I was brought on board.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.06,1:29:39.99,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Charming to the last.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.06,1:29:43.43,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We used to say, ''You can type\Nthis stuff, but you can't say it.''
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.23,1:29:49.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George didn't really like\Nbeing in London...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.24,1:29:51.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I suppose,\Nis the best way to say it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.57,1:29:53.73,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He doesn't like\Nbeing away from home.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.81,1:29:55.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He's not the most\Ngregarious person in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.24,1:29:58.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He had some clashes\Nwith the cameraman.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.51,1:30:03.68,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Gil Taylor was a very old-school\Ncameraman-- very crotchety.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.85,1:30:07.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George, coming out of\Nlow-budget filmmaking...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.12,1:30:10.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,was used to doing\Na lot of things himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.12,1:30:14.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So George would say things like,\N''Well, put a light here. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.46,1:30:17.26,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And Gil took offense\Nat that kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.33,1:30:19.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He says, ''That's not yourjob, son. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.73,1:30:24.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''You tell me what\Nyou want to see, and I'll do it...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.07,1:30:27.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the way I think is best\Nto create what you want to see.''
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.07,1:30:29.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was a clash\Nof style of working.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.38,1:30:31.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Slate 3 27, take four.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.64,1:30:33.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We're coming up\Non Alderaan.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.08,1:30:38.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I did feel something.\NI could almost see the remote.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.99,1:30:40.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.39,1:30:43.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You've taken your first step\Ninto a larger world.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.66,1:30:48.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas also became frustrated...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.70,1:30:51.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that the costumes, sets\Nand other production elements...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.90,1:30:54.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,weren't living up\Nto his vision for Star Wars.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.77,1:30:58.26,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The compromises required\Ndue to the film's budget...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.34,1:31:00.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,plagued him\Non an almost daily basis.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.67,1:31:03.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,What was disappointing\Nwould be the cantina sequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.38,1:31:06.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was really\Nimaginatively described...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.38,1:31:08.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and then you go in there...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.38,1:31:10.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and it looks like\NThe Nutcracker Suite.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.22,1:31:12.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There's a frog guy\Nand a mouse girl...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.45,1:31:16.18,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and a giant cricket at the bar.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.26,1:31:18.78,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was just really disappointing.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.39,1:31:22.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But George says, ''Don't worry.\NWe're gonna fix all of this. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.93,1:31:30.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We didn't see anything\Nof what ended up on the screen.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.17,1:31:32.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So when they blew my planet up...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.94,1:31:36.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I was looking at a guy going like this\Nagainst a board with a circle on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.71,1:31:38.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I mean, it was funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.38,1:31:40.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Proceed with the operation.\NYou may fire when ready.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.68,1:31:41.48,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.55,1:31:44.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Dantooine is too remote\Nto make an effective demonstration.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.32,1:31:47.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We will deal with your rebel friends\Nsoon enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.59,1:31:51.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Bang!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.63,1:31:55.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And you call yourselves humans.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.76,1:31:58.25,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George never talked.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.33,1:32:00.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We felt he wanted us\Nto hit our marks...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.93,1:32:03.37,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and magically\Naccommodate our dialogue.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.44,1:32:07.37,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He lost his voice at one point.\NWe didn't know that for days.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.44,1:32:10.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And we wanted to get him\Na little board that said...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.91,1:32:12.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''Faster and more intense.''
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.68,1:32:14.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That was his main direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.75,1:32:17.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Hejust wanted us\Nto speed through it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.42,1:32:20.28,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George is notorious\Nfor saying, after a take...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.35,1:32:22.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''Do it again.\NFaster, more intensity. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.59,1:32:26.12,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He certainly said to me, ''Terrific,\NTony. Can you do it again, faster?''
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.79,1:32:28.59,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But I didn't get\N''more intensity.''
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.66,1:32:31.53,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I didn't think 3PO with more intensity\Nwould be bearable. Do you?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.50,1:32:35.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I said all systems have been alerted\Nto your presence, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.77,1:32:38.43,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The main entrance seems\Nto be the only way in or out.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.50,1:32:40.90,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We all had to fill in\Na lot of the blanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.97,1:32:44.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was more a matter of, if we did\Nsomething he didn't like he'd tell us...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.01,1:32:48.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,rather than telling us what to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.28,1:32:49.91,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I think George likes people.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.98,1:32:53.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I think George\Nis a warmhearted person.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.79,1:32:57.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But, yeah, he's a little impatient\Nwith the process of acting...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.29,1:33:00.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,of finding something,\Nyou know.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.09,1:33:02.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He thinks it's there.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.09,1:33:04.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''It's right there.\NI wrote it down.'' You know?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.10,1:33:10.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''Do that.'' You know? And sometimes you\Ncan't just ''do that'' and make it work.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.84,1:33:13.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He's really focused on what he's\Ntrying to do and get everything right.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.04,1:33:16.91,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Is the smoke right?\NDid the squibs go off right?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.68,1:33:20.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And we were just\Ntaunting him mercilessly.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.08,1:33:23.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Carrie and Mark have\Nwicked sense ofhumors.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.02,1:33:25.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Carrie was very young...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.02,1:33:28.25,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and Mark was very young...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.45,1:33:30.25,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so they were\Nthe junior division...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.32,1:33:33.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and they were always\Nlurking about on set.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.83,1:33:36.69,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So it kept us in stitches.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.76,1:33:39.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I got one outfit\Nfor the first movie...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.63,1:33:41.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and as George taught me...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.63,1:33:43.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,there is no underwear in space.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.64,1:33:46.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Instead of that,\Nthere is gaffer tape.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.84,1:33:50.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So I was taped down.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.21,1:33:54.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And I used to say, we should just\Nmake up a contest on the call sheet...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.48,1:33:56.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,as to who's gonna rip it off.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.28,1:33:58.91,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But we didn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.99,1:34:03.12,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We were all goofing around\Nand trying to make George crack...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.19,1:34:05.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,'cause he looked like\Nhe was ready to burst into tears.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.46,1:34:07.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You'd try and cheer him up.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.83,1:34:09.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.50,1:34:16.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- Okay, cut.\N- Cut it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.24,1:34:17.73,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,- And?\N{\r原文字幕}- And?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.74,1:34:20.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Carrie and Mark bumped in too early.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.44,1:34:26.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The mike was in frame.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.01,1:34:28.78,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The mike was in picture.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.85,1:34:30.78,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The mike was in picture.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.85,1:34:34.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Go back to first positions.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.85,1:34:36.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The sound department\Nhas to pay up.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.86,1:34:39.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That, to him, was really\Ninappropriate humor at the time...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.86,1:34:42.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because I'm sure he's in the zone\Nand seeing what he wants to do...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.93,1:34:46.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and we're just actors\Ntrying to stave off boredom...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.73,1:34:50.69,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because we've been in\Nthe trash compactor all morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.77,1:34:52.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Ready? And action!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.41,1:34:55.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- What happened?\N- I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.41,1:34:57.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It just disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.44,1:35:00.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I got a really bad feeling\Nabout this.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.45,1:35:05.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But it is amazing what you can do\Nwhen you have a vision, an ambition...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.62,1:35:10.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and when you can bend\Nother people's will to your desire.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.59,1:35:13.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The thing that kept it focused\Ntowards the ambitions...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.59,1:35:16.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,was George's vision\Nand his passion for the idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.43,1:35:21.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the most memorable\Nstunt in Star Wars...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.37,1:35:24.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,was actually performed\Nby Mark Hamill and Carrie Fisher--
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.04,1:35:27.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the nick-of-time escape\Nof Luke and Leia...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.41,1:35:29.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,across a yawning chasm\Nin the Death Star.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.64,1:35:32.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Mark Hamill wanted to do\Nas much as he could himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.91,1:35:36.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I had times when I had to keep him back\Nbecause he was too enthusiastic.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.72,1:35:38.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He could've got hurt.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.28,1:35:40.98,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Princess Leia and Luke Skywalker\Nhad to swing over this void.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.05,1:35:44.99,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We couldn't afford doubles, so I said,\N''I can teach them. It'll be safe. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.06,1:35:49.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,My buddy and I, we put the harnesses on,\Nwe put the wires on.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.30,1:35:51.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Everyone down below.\NRemember, we are about 20 meters up...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.00,1:35:53.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,looking down on them.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.00,1:35:57.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And as we swung across\Nthere was a terrible tear.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.00,1:36:01.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,My buddy said to me,\N''Peter, your harness has snapped.''
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.47,1:36:03.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Mark said, ''I'm not going in that.\NIt's too dangerous. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.01,1:36:06.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,This is where I discovered\Nyou had to be a good liar.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.91,1:36:10.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I said, ''There's nothing wrong with the\Nharness. I split my pants as I landed. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.58,1:36:12.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He said, ''Oh, I thought\Nthat was the harness.''
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.62,1:36:14.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I said, ''I wouldn't let you\Ndo this if it was dangerous.''
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.02,1:36:16.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Action!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.39,1:36:24.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They did it in one take,\Nand that's how we got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.23,1:36:26.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,For luck.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.40,1:36:33.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That was really early on\Nin the shoot...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.41,1:36:37.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,when I was still\Nworried about my weight.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.41,1:36:41.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I thought we were gonna miss\Nand I'd hit the wall...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.08,1:36:46.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and they will say, ''Still too tubby.\NLet's bring in Jodie Foster.''
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.49,1:36:49.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Another of\NPeter Diamond's tasks...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.66,1:36:52.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,was choreographing\Nthe dramatic lightsaber battle...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.56,1:36:55.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,between Darth Vader\Nand Obi-Wan Kenobi.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.16,1:36:58.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You can't win, Darth.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.16,1:37:01.62,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,If my blade should find its mark,\Nyou will cease to exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.30,1:37:04.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But I warn you,\Nif you strike me down...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.80,1:37:08.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I shall become more powerful\Nthan you can possibly imagine.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.54,1:37:11.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George wanted a broadsword\Ntype of fight...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.24,1:37:13.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,with a touch ofJapanese behind it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.41,1:37:16.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But instead of becoming\Nsamurai moves with one hand...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.48,1:37:18.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I kept it with two hands...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.48,1:37:21.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,so all the moves were two hands,\Ncompletely like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.72,1:37:24.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The first swords\Nwere bits of wood...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.96,1:37:27.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,with front-projection material\Nwrapped around them.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.46,1:37:30.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Now, the hardest thing for me\Non the first fights--
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.46,1:37:33.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Darth Vader was a very heavy man...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.10,1:37:35.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Obi-Wan Kenobi was\Na gentleman, right...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.94,1:37:39.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,who had done some fencing\Nin the theater.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.47,1:37:42.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I had to teach them,\Nif that was a sword...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.17,1:37:44.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to stop before they touched,\N'cause the blades were breaking.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.78,1:37:48.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We broke so many blades.\NThey just kept snapping.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.75,1:37:55.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- Cut.\N- Cut it!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.49,1:38:00.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Across the Atlantic, Fox's head\Nof production, Alan Ladd,Jr....
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.89,1:38:02.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,continued to offer Lucas his main...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.03,1:38:05.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,if not his only,\Nsupport from the studio.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.97,1:38:08.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There was a lot of problems,yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.33,1:38:12.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Every board meeting I attended,\Nthe subject was always Star Wars.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.20,1:38:15.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''The costs are rising.\NIt's this, it's that.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.37,1:38:17.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Look, we've read drafts of scripts...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.68,1:38:20.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that make no sense to us\Nin any way, shape or form. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.61,1:38:22.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was rather unpleasant.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.42,1:38:26.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The things that stick in my mind\Nthat made me laugh were, like...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.42,1:38:29.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,memos worried about whether or not\Nthe Wookiee should have pants.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.52,1:38:31.18,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They're looking at this thing\Nand saying...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.26,1:38:33.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''Couldn't he have some lederhosen?''
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.89,1:38:37.73,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And I thought,\N''Isn't this great?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.80,1:38:40.26,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You know, of all the things\Nto worry about.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.33,1:38:42.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The Wookiee has no pants.''
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.00,1:38:45.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I think we were\Ntwo weeks over schedule.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.04,1:38:50.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,At that point, the board of directors\Nat Fox started to panic...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.34,1:38:55.91,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and tell Alan Ladd,Jr. that he had to\Nshut that film down regardless.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.98,1:38:58.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So he came to me and said...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.15,1:39:00.68,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''Look, you've gotta finish\Nin the next week...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.35,1:39:04.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because I've got another board meeting,\Nand I can't say we're still shooting.''
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.86,1:39:09.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I kept phoning their production\Ndepartment saying, ''This is insane.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.16,1:39:13.96,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,If we put on a second crew, it costs us\Nmore than going an extra week.''
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.03,1:39:16.37,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They said, ''It doesn't matter.\NThe studio's opinion...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.44,1:39:19.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,is that the day deadline is more\Nimportant than the money you spend.''
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.04,1:39:22.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The final scenes were filmed\Nat breakneck speed...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.88,1:39:24.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,with Lucas\Nfrantically bicycling...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.81,1:39:27.37,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,from one soundstage to another.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.45,1:39:31.78,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I think George suffered a lot more\Nthan I was aware of at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.85,1:39:33.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But I was very focused\Non what I was doing...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.02,1:39:37.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,'cause this was a very busy movie,\Njust nonstop dawn to dusk.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.89,1:39:39.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We did go over at the end...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.96,1:39:42.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and we split into three units\Nright at the end.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.83,1:39:45.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Gary directed the second unit...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.13,1:39:49.46,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and I had the distinction of directing\Nthe third unit of Star Wars.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.54,1:39:54.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,My shots were things like close-up\Nof R2-D2's third foot going down.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.94,1:39:58.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Nothing too dramatic.\NBut that's how we finished it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.14,1:39:59.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.31,1:40:04.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Okay, cut. Time up. Cut.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.52,1:40:07.97,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I hope that old man got the tractor beam\Ndown, or this is gonna be a short trip.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.05,1:40:09.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Hit it!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.89,1:40:14.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Fox originally slated Star Wars\Nfor a Christmas release in 1 976.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:14.86,1:40:16.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Schmuck.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.26,1:40:18.23,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,463, take one.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.30,1:40:21.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But the diffiicult shoot had put\Nthe film severely behind schedule.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.87,1:40:23.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Action.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.44,1:40:26.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- Didn't we just leave this party?\N- Give us a growl.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.01,1:40:30.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- What kept you?\N- We ran into some old friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.18,1:40:32.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- Is the ship all right?\N- Seems okay, if we can get to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.65,1:40:35.51,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I just hope the old man got\Nthe tractor beam out of commission.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.58,1:40:37.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- Look.\N- Now's our chance. Go!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.38,1:40:40.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,With barely six months to go...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.52,1:40:43.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,there was almost no chance\Nof delivering the project on time.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.52,1:40:44.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Okay, cut.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.79,1:40:47.78,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I hadjust finished shooting the movie,\Nand I was exhausted, basically...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.86,1:40:52.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but I had to go right from the shooting\Ninto the finishing without a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.63,1:40:56.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Already anxious\Nabout meeting his deadline...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.24,1:41:00.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas was shocked when he saw the first\Nassembly ofhis edited film that spring.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.24,1:41:02.37,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Sir, the groiters are losing power!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.44,1:41:04.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,All right. I'll get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.44,1:41:09.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The first cut of Star Wars\Nwas an unmitigated disaster.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.32,1:41:11.68,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- How's that?\N- Yes, that's much better.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.75,1:41:14.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'd started to see things cut together.\NI wasn't happy with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.65,1:41:17.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'd come in on weekends,\Nand I'd recut the film on my own.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.92,1:41:19.62,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Cut.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.69,1:41:21.68,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And I tried to get the editor\Nto cut it my way...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.76,1:41:25.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and he didn't really want to,\Nand so I had to let the editor go.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.36,1:41:27.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So I had no editor.\NI was behind schedule.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.87,1:41:29.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I had to race to finish the movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.87,1:41:31.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,1 77, take two.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.87,1:41:35.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas realized his only hope\Nwas to start from scratch.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.34,1:41:39.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And I am C-3PO,\Nhuman-cyborg relations.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.21,1:41:41.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And this is\Nmy counterpart, R2-D2.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.95,1:41:44.18,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- Oh, hello.\N- Okay, cut.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.12,1:41:48.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,To recut the movie, he hired\NPaul Hirsch and Richard Chew...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.92,1:41:52.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and for several months he was able\Nto borrow his wife, Marcia...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.42,1:41:55.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,who was editing New York, New York\Nwith Martin Scorsese.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.43,1:41:59.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Slate 250, take seven.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:59.50,1:42:00.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Action.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.70,1:42:04.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You must do what you feel\Nis right, of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.34,1:42:11.28,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Right now\NI don't feel too good.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.34,1:42:13.90,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,On Star Wars,\Nthe trio's first task...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.98,1:42:17.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,was to give the film an energy\Nand pace that was sorely lacking.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.72,1:42:18.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Cut.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.78,1:42:24.35,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was cut in a very traditional manner\Nofjust playing things out in masters...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.42,1:42:26.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and then going\Ninto the coverage...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.86,1:42:31.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and let the actors'rhythms\Ndictate the cuts...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.20,1:42:33.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,rather than having the cuts...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.20,1:42:36.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,kind of drive the rhythm of the scenes.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.10,1:42:39.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,21 1 , take three.\NGuide track.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.64,1:42:42.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Action!
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.14,1:42:46.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So consequently,\Nthere wasn't any excitement...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.75,1:42:49.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,in the footage the way\Nthat it had been put together.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.02,1:42:51.48,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Cut.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.55,1:42:53.28,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Richard and I would leapfrog.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.69,1:42:57.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,If he was on reel one,\NI would grab reel two.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.49,1:42:59.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Whoever finished that would\Ngrab reel three and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.84,1:43:14.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We used shots up until\Nthe very last frame.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.47,1:43:16.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- Cut.\N- Can I take another one?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.88,1:43:20.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Very often, the very next frame would be\Nthe flash of the camera stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.88,1:43:24.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,For instance, there's a shot\Nof one of the Sandpeople...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.62,1:43:28.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,who knocks Luke down, and then\Nhe holds his weapon up over his head.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:28.62,1:43:32.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He did it once. We rocked it back and\Nforth so he did it a number of times.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.16,1:43:41.46,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The only things that are there\Nis what's presentable...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.53,1:43:44.53,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and everything\Nbehind the scenes is a mess.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.84,1:43:49.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,With no chance\Nofbeing ready by Christmas...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.34,1:43:52.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,a new release date\Nwas set for summer, 1 977.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.48,1:43:55.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Some doubted that the movie\Nwould ever reach theaters.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.55,1:43:58.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But as bad as things\Nhad been with the editing...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.18,1:44:00.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the situation at ILM\Nwas even worse.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.39,1:44:05.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The company was trying to create effects\Nthat had never been done before.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:05.29,1:44:07.26,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They knew what they\Nwanted to accomplish...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.33,1:44:10.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but they had yet to create\Nanything usable for the film.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.36,1:44:12.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They had spent half their budget...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:12.97,1:44:16.23,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and ultimately I had about four shots,\Nnone of which I would accept.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.30,1:44:19.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They were just not good.\NThat was a low point.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.04,1:44:24.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I had no special effects. I didn't know\Nif we were gonna get the ships to work.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.08,1:44:26.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So it was a pretty desperate time.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.08,1:44:29.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And we'd spent half the budget\Nbuilding the motion-control cameras...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.48,1:44:31.28,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and setting the shop up.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:31.35,1:44:34.98,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was a disaster to say the least.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.15,1:44:37.68,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The factory has to be built...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.76,1:44:41.19,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,before the first can of peas\Ncan be sent to the supermarket.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.26,1:44:43.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And I think it was a year or more...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.60,1:44:47.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,without any film coming out,\Nwithout one shot being finished.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.30,1:44:49.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,'Cause they were building\Noptical printers and cameras.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.54,1:44:52.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We were building models.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.40,1:44:54.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I know that George was\Ndisappointed in the work...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.94,1:44:57.97,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,and I'm disappointed\N{\r原文字幕}that he was disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.44,1:45:01.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But there's a certain subjectivity\Nto some of that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.55,1:45:05.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I wish he'd been happier,\Nbut I also think that ultimately...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.02,1:45:07.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the work did thejob.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.63,1:45:22.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,When word of the postproduction problems\Nreached the Fox board of directors...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.10,1:45:26.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,they decided they'd had enough of\NGeorge Lucas and ''that science movie. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.87,1:45:29.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I just sat in one\Nexecutive committee meeting...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:30.01,1:45:31.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,where they're hauling me\Nover the coals.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.01,1:45:34.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I just said,\N''It's the greatest picture ever made.''
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.38,1:45:36.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That ended the conversation.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.38,1:45:40.65,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They were afraid to say,\N''Well,you're stupid and you're wrong...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.72,1:45:43.75,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and we want you out of this building\Nby 5:00 this afternoon. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.99,1:45:48.98,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There were some tense moments there.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.83,1:45:51.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,With the dismal\Nearly cut of the film...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.83,1:45:55.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,ILM in chaos and growing pressure\Nfrom the studio...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.33,1:45:59.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas was facing almost\Nunbearable battles on a daily basis.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:00.14,1:46:02.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,After an especially\Ntense trip to ILM...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.01,1:46:05.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas felt sharp chest pains.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.51,1:46:09.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Fearing a heart attack, the director\Nchecked into a Marin County hospital.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:09.58,1:46:12.78,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,He was diagnosed with\Nhypertension and exhaustion...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:12.85,1:46:14.98,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and was warned\Nto reduce his stress level.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.05,1:46:17.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,At that point, I really felt...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.16,1:46:21.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'd gotten myself into a real mess and\Ndidn't know whether I was gonna get out.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:22.06,1:46:24.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas doubled his efforts\Nto save Star Wars.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.43,1:46:28.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The situation at ILM\Nrequired drastic measures.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:28.83,1:46:31.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,To get the film's crucial\Nspecial effects back on track...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.84,1:46:35.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas had no choice\Nbut to step in personally.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:35.37,1:46:38.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We put a production department in\Nat the special effects company.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.18,1:46:39.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I went there twice a week.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:39.75,1:46:42.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There was a certain amount\Nof resentment at first...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.21,1:46:44.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because they felt...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.82,1:46:48.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that they were being challenged a bit\Non how they had set it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.79,1:46:52.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We felt that there was a certain\Nquasi-hippie mentality...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.79,1:46:55.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that some of them had\Nabout the schedule.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:55.46,1:46:57.69,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Ultimately, I guess\Nwe were known as a country club.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.76,1:47:00.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I think it looked to those guys\Nthat there needed to be...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.93,1:47:03.59,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,a really strong\Nproduction force in there...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.67,1:47:07.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that was going to meet\Nsome sort of quota.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.94,1:47:13.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,With hundreds of shots\Nleft to be completed...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:13.38,1:47:17.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,ILM would have to do a year's worth\Nof work in just six months.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.42,1:47:20.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But Lucas and Kurtz were determined\Nto turn the situation around.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:25.82,1:47:28.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Gary was a gearhead,\Nso he could understand our problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:28.56,1:47:31.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And George is a storyteller...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.40,1:47:33.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and so we have to serve his needs...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.93,1:47:36.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because he's the one\Nthat's telling the story.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:36.57,1:47:39.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But we had to build these incredible\Ncontraptions in order to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:41.74,1:47:43.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George was our general.\NWe're his soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.01,1:47:46.57,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And we're all\Nfighting this single battle...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:46.65,1:47:48.31,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,to get this film out.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.38,1:47:49.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We were on the front lines...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.02,1:47:53.47,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and that gave us also\Nkind of a feeling of being special...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:53.55,1:47:58.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and fighting this great battle\Nto get this thing done, whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.06,1:48:03.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Luke, pull up.!
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.13,1:48:07.46,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,To help inspire\Nthe effects team at ILM...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.87,1:48:11.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas had spliced together aerial\Ndogfights from old war movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.97,1:48:15.24,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That would be like the first animatic,\Nwhich you do in the computer now...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:15.31,1:48:19.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and we matched frame to frame and\Nthe action on that as close as we could.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.18,1:48:24.98,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was hugely helpful.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:26.95,1:48:30.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- I got him.!\N- Great, kid! Don't get cocky.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.36,1:48:34.59,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,To describe that abstract world\Nof a battle is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.66,1:48:38.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Storyboards don't do it, as far as the\Npacing, the rhythms that he needed.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:42.43,1:48:44.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- Thanks, Wedge.\N- That was great.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:53.98,1:48:57.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,As fall turned to winter, Star Wars\Nfinally started to take shape.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:57.72,1:48:59.12,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That's it! We did it!
Dialogue: 0,1:48:59.18,1:49:00.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:01.59,1:49:04.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Working from\Nthe raw production tracks...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:05.36,1:49:09.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,sound designer Ben Burtt would add\Na critical new layer to the film.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.16,1:49:12.65,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Burtt had spent a year\Nbuilding a catalog of sounds...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:12.73,1:49:15.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,for things that didn't exist\Nin our galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:18.57,1:49:22.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George introduced the idea of what\Nhe called an ''organic sound track. ''
Dialogue: 0,1:49:22.74,1:49:26.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George thought that Chewbacca\Nmight be made up...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:26.95,1:49:29.88,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,from recordings of dogs\Nor maybe even bears.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.95,1:49:35.01,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In addition, I recorded some lions\Nand tigers and even some walruses.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.89,1:49:39.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I would begin\Nediting them together...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:39.36,1:49:42.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and making little phrases\Nout of the noises.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.16,1:49:44.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I would take the recordings\Nand edit the best pieces.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:47.33,1:49:49.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You know, the bear might make\Na sound that sounded angry.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:51.37,1:49:53.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Or they might make a sound\Nthat was cute.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:57.04,1:50:00.91,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Or a sound like a sentence--\Na ''wah, wah'' kind of a sound.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:03.15,1:50:04.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You said it, Chewie.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:04.92,1:50:08.48,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The voice of R2 turned out to be\Nthe most difficult problem to solve...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:08.55,1:50:10.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,in the sound design\Nof the first movie...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:11.49,1:50:14.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,because R2 had to act\Nalongside of the other actors.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:14.86,1:50:17.06,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And the script only said...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:17.13,1:50:20.19,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that R2 made a sound,\Nor maybe R2 beeped.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:21.00,1:50:23.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I had a small\Nelectronic synthesizer...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:23.84,1:50:27.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and I did some patches with it\Nand made up some electronic sounds.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:27.34,1:50:29.27,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But that didn't sound alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:29.34,1:50:32.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,At one point we talked\Nabout R2's personality...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:32.08,1:50:36.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and we felt he was developing\Nkind of as a toddler.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:37.88,1:50:39.82,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So I did a lot\Nofbaby recordings...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:39.89,1:50:43.65,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and eventually we found that\Nin the discussion of R2's voice...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.72,1:50:45.66,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,we were making\Nthe sounds ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:47.39,1:50:51.69,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,A few experiments led to\Nthe combination of using my voice...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:51.76,1:50:54.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,doing baby talk--\Nbeeps and boops--
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.03,1:50:58.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,with the electronic synthesizer.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.37,1:51:01.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So R2 is sort of 50% machine\Nand 50% organic...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:02.11,1:51:05.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,coming out of\Nthe performance of a person.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:07.31,1:51:12.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The breathing for Vader was recorded\Nby putting a little tiny microphone...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:12.45,1:51:15.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,down inside\Na regulator on a scuba tank.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:17.49,1:51:22.22,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I breathed through the mask itself,\Nand it breathed in and out...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:22.29,1:51:25.99,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and out of that came the various\Npaces of Vader breathing.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:27.40,1:51:30.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And that sound worked out\Npretty successfully.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:34.14,1:51:37.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Finding the right voice for Darth Vader\Nwas another challenge.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.34,1:51:40.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And action!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:40.15,1:51:44.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Lucas never intended to use the on-set\Nvocal performance of David Prowse.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:45.75,1:51:49.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Start tearing this ship apart, piece\Nby piece, until you find those tapes!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:49.49,1:51:52.65,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Find the passengers in this vessel!\NI want them alive!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:52.72,1:51:55.16,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I can still hear\NDavid Prowse's accent...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:55.66,1:51:59.26,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,in the Darth Vader mask, muffled,\N'cause he would do the real dialogue...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:59.33,1:52:01.60,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,in trying to curse\NCarrie Fisher or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:01.67,1:52:03.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I don't know what\Nyou're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:03.40,1:52:05.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'm a member of the Imperial Senate\Non a diplomatic mission--
Dialogue: 0,1:52:05.84,1:52:10.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You are part of the Rebel Alliance\Nand a traitor. Take her away!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:10.18,1:52:12.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was hilarious and terrifying\Nat the same time...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:12.61,1:52:14.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,'cause we didn't know\Nwhat Darth sounded like.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:14.65,1:52:17.77,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That was the first time we heard him.\NWe were like, ''Is that it?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:17.85,1:52:20.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Is he gonna be some Scottish guy,\Nor what is this?''
Dialogue: 0,1:52:20.95,1:52:25.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Prowse's voice would later be replaced\Nwith a more menacing performance...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:25.39,1:52:30.09,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,provided by classically trained\Nstage and film actorJames Earl Jones.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.80,1:52:33.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,George had hired David Prowse...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:34.27,1:52:37.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but he said he wanted\Na so-called ''darker'' voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.17,1:52:41.43,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,Not in terms of ethnic,\N{\r原文字幕}but in terms of timbre.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:42.11,1:52:44.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The rumor is that he thought\Nof Orson Welles...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:46.14,1:52:50.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and then probably thought that Orson\Nmight be too recognizable.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:51.02,1:52:54.98,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So what he ends up is picking\Na voice that was born in Mississippi...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:55.05,1:52:57.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,raised in Michigan, and was a stutterer.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:58.22,1:53:00.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And that happened\Nto be my voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:00.93,1:53:03.83,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I want to know what happened\Nto the plans they sent you.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:03.90,1:53:05.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I don't know what\Nyou're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:05.96,1:53:09.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I'm a member of the Imperial Senate\Non a diplomatic mission to Alderaan.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:09.47,1:53:12.33,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You are part of\Nthe Rebel Alliance and a traitor.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:12.40,1:53:13.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Take her away!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:14.17,1:53:18.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,C-3PO's voice struck us all as\N''We've got to do something about that.''
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.68,1:53:20.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Thirty-four, take three.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:20.88,1:53:23.91,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We seem to be made to suffer.\NIt's our lot in life.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:23.98,1:53:26.04,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was mentioned\Na number of times...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:26.12,1:53:28.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that C-3PO might sound\Nlike a used car salesman.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.72,1:53:30.78,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Not the English butler type.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:30.86,1:53:33.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry, sir.\NI must have fallen over.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:33.76,1:53:39.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I just came up with this voice\Nof an over-the-top British butler.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:40.07,1:53:43.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,British because that would\Nbe my natural mode of thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:43.07,1:53:46.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,A butler because\Nthat was his role in life.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:46.50,1:53:49.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Nervous because that\Nwas his feeling in life.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.74,1:53:52.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And it came as, ''C-3PO,\Nhuman-cyborg relations.''
Dialogue: 0,1:53:53.01,1:53:55.34,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,This is my counterpart,\NR2-D2.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:56.05,1:53:57.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:57.68,1:53:59.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,A few people\Nwere brought in to record...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:59.88,1:54:02.65,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and an attempt was made\Nto see how 3PO would be...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:02.72,1:54:04.65,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,with different kinds of voices.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:04.72,1:54:08.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I believe 30 actors coming,\Nand some really quite impressive names.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:08.53,1:54:11.98,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Stan Freberg and a few others\Nwere auditioned.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:12.06,1:54:15.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Apparently one of them\Nwas a major cartoon actor...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:15.57,1:54:18.56,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,a man of literally a thousand voices,\Nwho eventually said...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:18.64,1:54:22.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,''You know something, George, Tony's\Nvoice is pretty good for the character.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.27,1:54:24.21,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Why don't you\Njust use his voice?''
Dialogue: 0,1:54:24.28,1:54:27.07,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And eventually the discussion\Njust quieted down...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:27.15,1:54:29.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and it was an\Nexcellent performance.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:29.28,1:54:31.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It synchronized\Nwith his body motions.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.48,1:54:33.71,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was a total character\Nwhich he created.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:33.79,1:54:35.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,His track was left in the movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:36.39,1:54:39.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- Hey. We don't serve their kind here.\N- What?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:39.92,1:54:42.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Your droids-- they'll have to wait\Noutside. We don't want them here.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:42.96,1:54:45.12,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Wait out by the speeder.\NWe don't want any trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:45.20,1:54:46.86,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I heartily agree with you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:49.77,1:54:50.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Cut.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:50.87,1:54:52.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,428, take seven.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:52.87,1:54:54.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Action.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:54.27,1:54:57.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Here we go.\NCut in the sublight engines.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:00.71,1:55:02.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,At long last,\Nthe editing, sound...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.75,1:55:05.84,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and visual effects\Nwere taking shape.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:08.02,1:55:11.89,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,But a private screening of the film\Nfor Lucas's closest friends...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:11.96,1:55:14.08,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,didn't do much\Nto bolster his confidence.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:15.26,1:55:20.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was an early stage, you know,\Nsort of a second or third cut.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:20.77,1:55:23.79,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I had a couple of my friends\Ncome up to see it.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.87,1:55:26.20,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Brian De Palma was in town.\NSteven came.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:26.27,1:55:28.36,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Some other friends\Ncame to see it.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:28.44,1:55:30.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,The human characters\Nand the sets were there...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:30.84,1:55:35.80,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but, of course, all the spectacular--\Nyou know, the Death Star fight...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:36.48,1:55:38.38,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and the battle inside the trench...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.45,1:55:42.11,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and all that was just...\Nnot even there to be seen.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:45.19,1:55:48.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So, the reaction was not\Na good one. I loved the movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:48.09,1:55:50.69,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I was one of the only people\Nin the audience that liked the movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:50.76,1:55:54.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,All my friends were very honest:\N''I don't get it. What are you doing?''
Dialogue: 0,1:55:54.70,1:55:57.17,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,That was basically\Nthe tenor of the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:57.24,1:55:59.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,\Nthe studio and Laddie...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:59.47,1:56:01.70,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and his little group\Nsaw the film.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:01.77,1:56:05.40,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They loved it. It was the first time\NI've actually shown a film...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:05.48,1:56:08.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and one of the executives\Neven cried at the screening.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:08.21,1:56:09.91,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It was very emotional for him.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:11.12,1:56:15.75,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I sat my family round\Nthe kitchen table in my house...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:15.82,1:56:18.19,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and I said, ''The most extraordinary\Nday of my life...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:18.59,1:56:22.25,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,has just taken place,\Nand I want you to remember this day.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:23.19,1:56:25.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Because this is what I never dreamed--\Nor maybe I dreamed--
Dialogue: 0,1:56:25.80,1:56:28.46,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but I never thought I would have\Na day's experience...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:28.53,1:56:30.90,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,like the day I've had today\Nin seeing this film.''
Dialogue: 0,1:56:30.97,1:56:33.87,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I couldn't even believe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:33.94,1:56:36.81,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,At that point I was used to studio\Nchiefs saying, ''This is terrible.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:36.87,1:56:39.00,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't show this to\Nan audience. Embarrassing.''
Dialogue: 0,1:56:39.68,1:56:44.41,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,So, it was very rewarding to show it to\Npeople, even though it was in bad shape.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:44.48,1:56:49.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,It didn't help that one critical\Nelement in Star Wars was still missing--
Dialogue: 0,1:56:49.45,1:56:50.39,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,There's no lock.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:52.06,1:56:54.02,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,the musical score.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:54.69,1:56:57.32,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,- That oughta hold them for a while.\N- Quick. We've got to get across.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:57.40,1:57:00.63,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,-Find the controls to extend the bridge.\N-I think I just blasted it.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:00.70,1:57:02.50,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,They're coming through!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:03.40,1:57:07.90,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I remember bugging George.\N''When can we hear the score?''
Dialogue: 0,1:57:08.64,1:57:11.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Fortunately, Lucas was able\Nto recruit...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:11.21,1:57:15.15,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,one of the industry's most accomplished\Ncomposers,John Williams.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:15.81,1:57:19.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Williams had recently won an Oscar\Nfor Steven Spielberg's Jaws...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:20.12,1:57:23.95,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,and his resume included countless film\Nand television scores...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:24.62,1:57:28.29,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,including music for the original\NLost in Space television series.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:30.26,1:57:33.49,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,I do remember George\Ntalking about the fact...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:33.56,1:57:36.03,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,that what we were going to see\Nin the film...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:36.10,1:57:38.26,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,represents worlds\Nthat we hadn't seen...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:38.94,1:57:42.30,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,but that the music should give us\Nsome kind of an emotional anchor.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:44.44,1:57:47.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We heard a romantic melody\Nfor Princess Leia.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:48.01,1:57:51.74,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,We heard bellicose music\Nfor the battle scenes.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:54.72,1:57:58.85,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,And some very heavy\Ndeclamatory thing for Darth Vader.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:02.23,1:58:03.92,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,In March, 1 977...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:04.00,1:58:06.93,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,John Williams led\Nthe London Symphony Orchestra...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:07.00,1:58:09.83,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,in the performance\Nof the Star Wars soundtrack.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:09.90,1:58:12.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,Recorded over 1 2 days, it was\Na sweeping symphonic masterpiece...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:12.61,1:58:16.55,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,one of the few things to actually\Nexceed Lucas's expectations.

